title: anise kringle rolls
directions: Scald milk, cool to lukewarm (105 degrees), add yeast and stir to dissolve.
Add sugar, salt, butter, eggs and seeds to milk mixture.
Gradually add flour, mixing after each addition.
Use mixer with dough hook if you have one or, if not, when stiff enough, turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl, cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and shape into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 375 for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Then add vanilla, lemon and milk.
Mix in eggs one at a time.
Add 4 cups of cake flour; mix well.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan for 2 hours at 300°.
Do not preheat oven.

title: *zucchini cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix with the creamed ingredients.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Cool right side up on rack.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: To melted butter, add garlic, parsley, paprika, cayenne and cooking sherry.
Mix.
Add bread crumbs and toss.
Place shrimp in baking dish.
Spoon the butter mixture over.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until crumbs brown.
Sprinkle with additional chopped parsley before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: portuguese potato casserole
directions: Cube cooled cooked potatoes; do not peel.
Cube cheese and mix with potatoes in large casserole dish.
Add onion, pimento and parsley.
Top with croutons and pour melted margarine over top. Season with paprika and onion salt.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cup boiling water. Stir in berries with juice and sugar; cool until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cut cake into 1/2-inch slice and place in bottom of 9 x 13 loaf pan; next put 1/2 jello mixture over cake and repeat layers.
Refrigerate.
You could break cake into pieces and mix with jello also.

title: better than baseball cake or kevin costner cake
directions: Bake cake. Let cool completely. Use end of wooden spoon. Poke holes throughout cake. Mix caramel topping, crushed Heath bars (save about 1/4 cup), sweetened milk. Pour mixture over cake and top with Cool Whip. Spread out evenly. Sprinkle remaining crushed Heath bars on top. Refrigerate.

title: pork chops with lemon and rosemary(quick main dish that works on chicken too)
directions: Squeeze 1 tablespoon juice from the lemon and sprinkle the juice over the pork chops.
Crush the rosemary between your fingers and sprinkle it over the chops with pepper.
Let the chops stand while preparing the grill for direct heat.
Sprinkle the pork chops with salt and grill until just slightly pink near the bone, 5 to 7 minutes per side.

title: honey mustard baste
directions: Mix all ingredients together and brush on grilled zucchini, onions or steak.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Fry tortillas until hot and bubbling. Alternate in layers: tortillas, cheese, chili, chicken and onion. Pour soup and milk over top. Place in lightly greased casserole bowl. Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbling. Feeds 6 cowboys or 8 city slickers.

title: peaches-n-cream pie
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin and boiling water.
Cool until syrupy. Beat with rotary beater until frothy.
Add peaches and lemon juice.
Stir into jello mixture.
When thick, fold in whipped cream and beat until stiff.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: russian fluff
directions: Fry meats with onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook rice and, when done, add peas, mushrooms and thinned tomato juice.
Mix meat mixture and rice mixture together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake for one hour in moderate oven.
Strips of bacon can be placed across top, if desired.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cut in shortening into dry ingredients. Combine beaten egg, orange juice and orange peel and add to dry ingredients.
Mix just to moisten.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Bake one hour until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack before removing from pan.
Wrap and store overnight to develop flavors before slicing.

title: orange-coconut bubble bread
directions: Cut dough into 16 equal pieces; shape each in a ball.
Place on floured surface.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
In shallow dish, mix coconut, sugar and orange peel.
Using two spoons, roll balls in melted butter, then in coconut mixture to coat all sides. Arrange loosely in two layers in a greased tube pan.
Cover; let rise in warm, draft-free place about 30 minutes or until double. Bake in center of preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert immediately on rack.
Turn top side up.

title: cranberry handpies
directions: In large bowl, stir apple pie filling, fresh apples, cranberries, walnuts and lemon peel; mix and set aside.
Roll prepared pie crusts into 11-inch rounds.
Cut 4 (4-inch) circles. Set scraps aside for decorations.
Will have 16 circles.
Work with 2 circles at a time and refrigerate remaining between wax paper.
Place 1/2 cup filling in center of one circle.
Beat egg yolk with water.
Brush egg mixture on edges of circles.
Place second circle on top and use fingers to seal.
Lift carefully onto large ungreased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate remainder while fitting 4 to 8 on cookie sheet.
Brush all pies with remaining egg wash; sprinkle each with sugar and refrigerate 10 minutes. Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pies for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking soda and powder, salt and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch cake pan and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until done. Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: hamburger bean pie
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in salt, pepper, beans and soup.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Keep hot in oven while preparing topping.

title: my favorite cucumber salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cucumbers and onions; set aside.
In a large saucepan, mix together the vinegar, sugar, garlic, oil, salt and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Pour mixture over the cucumbers and onion; add the pepper and dill and mix well. Keep refrigerated.
Serve well chilled.
This may be stored in refrigerator for up to 4 days.

title: raisin-pecan sandwich spread
directions: Cook egg yolks, lemon juice and sugar in top of double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise, nuts and raisins.
Spread on bread.
Cut in 1/2 or 1/4 sandwiches.

title: crusty beef cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oil. Add onion and cook until golden. Add meat and cook until meat loses its color. Add spaghetti sauce; simmer. Arrange in a large casserole dish (4 1/2-quart) half of the noodles, half of the sauce, half of the cheese.
Repeat layers. This can be prepared the night before. Cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: risotto
directions: Risotto is Italian rice arborio.
It soaks up the flavors of whatever you cook with it!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach, drain and set aside.
Combine cheese and oleo. Beat in mixer until smooth.
Stir in spinach.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add milk and flour alternately, starting with flour and ending with flour. Add baking powder and vanilla and beat well. Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingrediments...mix in other...bake in a tube pan...put in a cold oven, turn to 350° 'n leave in fur 1 hr 'n 10 minutes...remove frum pan whilst still hot.

title: garden vegetable dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cottage cheese and milk until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill at least 1 hour. Serve with crisp cold vegetables. Makes about 1 cup.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for one hour.
Leave uncovered.
Melt 2 ounces of shredded Cheddar cheese on top before serving.

title: layered salad
directions: Shred lettuce in large flat dish.
Layer on onion, green pepper, celery, carrots and frozen peas (straight from package). Mix sugar into the mayonnaise; spread over the peas.
Top that with a sprinkle of bacon bits and grated cheese.

title: stuffed ham rolls
directions: Combine spinach, stuffing mix and sour cream.
Spread 1/4 cup of stuffing mixture down center of ham slice.
Roll up and place seam side down in single layer in 12 x 8 1/2-inch baking dish. Melt butter in saucepan, blend in flour.
Add milk.
Heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, and stir until cheese melts.
Pour over ham rolls.
Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes more. Serve hot with sauce spooned over ham rolls.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles; mix sauce with meat.
Separately mix all other ingredients with cottage cheese.
Layer the ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:
Sauce, 4 noodles across, cottage cheese mix, 3 noodles, sauce, 4 noodles, cottage cheese, 4 noodles, sauce. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 350° for one hour, covered with foil.

title: old fashion flour gravy
directions: Place flour and sausage drippings in pan.
Stir continually, until brown.
Add milk and water.
Stir until thickened.
If too thick, add a few tablespoons of water.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Add bouillon cubes to chicken as it cooks.
When done, bone chicken.
Spread in bottom of 10-inch baking dish.
Prepare dressing mix according to directions on box, except use chicken broth for the liquid; set aside.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Scrape larger seed out of cucumbers.
Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process, then chill for several hours before serving.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.

title: 8 minute light and fruity pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, stirring, about 3 minutes. Add ice cubes.
Stir constantly until gelatin is thickened (2 or 3 minutes).
Remove unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in Cool Whip.
Chill until mixture will mound.
Pour into crust.
Let set. Keep in refrigerator.

title: ham and pepper stir-fry
directions: For sauce, combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
In wok, stir-fry vegies in oil on high.
Add ham and heat through.
Push all to sides.
Pour sauce in center.
Cook until thick and bubbly. Serve with or over rice.

title: prune pie
directions: Cook prunes.
Add sugar to taste.
Seed and mash prunes.
Just cover bottom of crust.
Beat eggs; add sugar, butter, flour, salt, milk and vanilla.
Fill crust with custard.
Bake at 400° for first few minutes until custard begins to set.
Lower temperature to 200° and bake until done (about one hour).

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, 1/3 cup sugar, oil, baking powder, salt, egg and 2 to 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto well floured board; knead until smooth, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Roll these halves into rectangles. Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, 4 teaspoons cinnamon and 4 tablespoons oleo and spread on rectangles.
Roll up halves, beginning at wide side.
Pinch edge of dough to seal.
Heat brown sugar (packed) and 1/2 cup oleo until sugar melts.
Remove from heat (stir in Karo, if desired).
Divide this mixture into two parts and spread over bottom of 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pans.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over this.
Cut rolls into 3/4-inch slices, placing slightly apart in pans.
Let rise in warm place until rolls have doubled in size. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Immediately invert pan on large tray.
Let pans remain over rolls 1 to 2 minutes so caramel drizzles over rolls.

title: homemade pastry for tarts and pies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with a fork and knife or use a pastry blender.
Mixture should resemble coarse meal.
Sprinkle cold water (1 tablespoon at a time) evenly over surface.
Stir with a fork.
Shape pastry into a ball.

title: apple cake from gram sommer's
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first.
Then cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy with electric beater and then add small amount of flour at a time.
Beat after each cup of flour.
This will be quite stiff.
Then add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° until tested done.
Makes 2 small or 1 large cake.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix.
Mix well. Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: deli salad
directions: Drain and combine
the	green beans, yellow beans, lima beans, green pepper, onion
and pimento in a large glass bowl. Combine vinegar and
remaining
ingredients
in
jar.
Cover; shake vigorously.
Pour dressing over bean mixture; toss well. Cover. Let it
marinate
overnight in the refrigerator before serving. Stir occasionally.	Makes about 8 cups.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; set aside.
Brown hamburger, sausage, onion, pepper, pepperoni or anything else you like on a pizza.
Add mushrooms and pizza sauce and spread on top of macaroni and cheese; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baconized corn muffins
directions: Sift flour once before measuring.
Sift flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Beat egg and add milk.
Combine with flour mixture.
Add melted shortening and beat well.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle tops with uncooked diced bacon.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven, then set muffins under broiler so that bacon may become crisp.
Yield: 8 muffins.

title: rhubarb dream dessert
directions: Blend together the first 3 ingredients for a crust.
Press into an ungreased 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked apples(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Take a small rectangular Pyrex dish and lightly grease the bottom with a little margarine or butter.
Core the apples all the way through, and peel away the skin from around the top of the apple.
Slice a small piece from the bottom of the apple so that it will stand up straight in the baking pan.
Place the apples in the pan.
Mix the sugar and butter/margarine with the raisins and place in the cored-out cavity of each apple. Place in the oven and bake for approximately 20 minutes.

title: walnut carrot cake
directions: Chop 1/2 cup walnuts extra fine.
Grease three 9-inch layer cake pans (or tins for 18 muffins) well. Sprinkle each with walnuts to coat. Chop remaining walnuts coarsely; set aside. Re-sift flour with baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, eggs, oil and spices. Beat at high speed until light and well mixed.
Add 1/2 of the flour mixture; blend well. Add milk, then remaining flour.
Stir in carrots and walnuts (and raisins, if desired).
Divide batter evenly between pans.

title: easy greek salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: delicious pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Pour whole bottle of salad dressing over pasta while it's still hot. Add spice.
Also cut up and add any vegetables you want (broccoli, tomatoes, mushrooms, onions, zucchini).
Makes a pretty salad and always better on the second day.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice meat with the grain as thin as possible into strips. (Ask your butcher to do this for you, it's really hard to get really thin slices yourself.)
Put all ingredients into large bowl and let marinate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer boneless chicken breasts over the bottom of your dish.
Cover chicken with cheese slices.
Spread cream of chicken soup over cheese and sprinkle with about 1/4 cup water over soup.
Make Stove Top stuffing as directed.
Spread over chicken soup.
Cover lightly with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil last 15 minutes of cooking.
Can be prepared the night before.
Just refrigerate.

title: patio punch
directions: Combine punch and lemon juice.

Spoon about half the ice cream into 10 glasses. Add half the punch mixture with the ice cream. Add remaining punch with ginger ale and pour into glasses. Top each one with a scoop of ice cream. Trim with lemon peel.

title: coffee-spice cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and egg yolks.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and spices.
Add alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lite granny's chocolate cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, stir together milk, prunes, vanilla, egg whites or egg substitutes and coffee.
Pour moist ingredients into dry ingredients, blending well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) round baking pans.
Bake at 350° between 30 to 35 minutes until center tests done with wooden pick. Frost cake or just dust with powdered sugar.

title: nutmeg cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake in greased 15 x 9 x 3-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and heat juice with marshmallows until melted. Dissolve Jell-O in this and let cool. Add cottage cheese, pineapple, pecans and whipped topping.

title: no-fat healthy coleslaw
directions: Combine yogurt, vinegar and honey in a large bowl.
Add vegetables and mix well.
Cover and chill 15 minutes.

title: peppermint marble angel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare batter following package directions.
Stir in peppermint extract.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, milk and oil;
pour into a greased shallow 3 qt. baking dish.
In a bowl combine cherries, food coloring, extract and remaining sugar;
spoon over batter.	Bake at 375° for 40-45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the cake portion comes out clean. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream if desired.
Yield: 10-12 servings.
Kids love to watch this one bake because the cherries sink to the bottom and the cake part rises to the top.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Place tamales in lightly greased baking dish.
Mix hominy, onion and mushroom soup.
Pour over tamales.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly and tamales are hot.

title: mushroom surprise
directions: Saute mushrooms, coarsely sliced, in butter, just enough to smell like mushrooms.
Butter 3 slices white bread, cut in 1-inch squares and line casserole.

Combine mushrooms with 1/2 cup each: chopped celery, onion, green pepper and mayonnaise, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 3 more slices of buttered bread. Pour eggs, slightly beaten with milk.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
One hour before serving, spoon a can of undiluted mushroom soup over it.
Bake at 300° for 60 to 70 minutes or at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
About 10 minutes before it's done, sprinkle grated yellow cheese on top.

title: ranch chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the cornflakes, Parmesan cheese and salad dressing mix. Dip chicken in butter, then roll in cornflake mixture to coat. Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: lo-fat lo-cal veggie muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Spoon into well greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: banana slush
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Separate in 3 different containers. Freeze until ready to use.
When ready to use, thaw for one hour before use.
Mix 2 bottles of ginger ale, Sprite or 7-Up with one container of frozen mixture.

title: scallops a la sea
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs and butter.
Top with bread crumbs mixed with the butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese. Pour into large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: miracle pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend well.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chicken and lemon
directions: In a skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add garlic, rosemary and sage.
Cook until garlic is soft.
Remove rosemary sprig.
Add chicken.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Pour in lemon juice.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon juices over chicken to serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil cloves and cinnamon 20 minutes in 1 pint of water.
Add tea to 2 pints of boiling water and seep 15 minutes.
Combine in gallon jar and add water to make full gallon.
Refrigerate. Delicious hot or cold.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pat out cookie dough to 10-inch circle on greased pizza pan.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes, until golden brown. Cool.
Stir powdered sugar into cream cheese.
Spread over cookie to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Spoon pie filling over cream cheese. Cut into wedges.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jocelyn's english shortbread bars
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Mixture will be crumbly. Press this into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Decorate with sprinkled cinnamon or sugar when cool.

title: light chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray an 8-inch square pan with vegetable oil cooking spray.
In a medium saucepan over low heat, melt spread.
Add sugar; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat; stir in cocoa and vanilla.
Add egg substitute; stir to blend.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 25 minutes or until edges begin to pull away from pan.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine. Pour soup over meatballs.
Cover tightly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Scoop out insides of bread.
Stuff with mixture.

title: smunchies
directions: Mix pudding and all milk.
Mix peanut butter into pudding. Put 2 teaspoons pudding mixture onto each of 36 graham crackers. Top with other cracker and freeze.
When frozen, wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Return to freezer.

title: fruit medley punch
directions: *Ice ring is optional and should be prepared in advance.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Stir together the flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Beat the butter for 30 seconds.
Add 2 cups sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well. Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture until well combined.
Form dough balls of 1-inch size.
Roll in a mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Place balls 2 inches apart on cookie sheet; flatten slightly with the bottom of a drinking glass.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 8 minutes, or until light golden.
Makes about 66.

title: squash and carrot casserole
directions: Combine bread crumbs with butter.
Place 1/2 bread crumbs on bottom of a greased 9 x 9-inch dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients and place over the layer of bread crumbs.
Top with remaining 1/2 of bread crumbs.
Cover and bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Cream together 1 cup sugar and 1 cup butter.
Add eggs, 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Pat 2/3 of the mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: ted's soused shrimp
directions: In a saute pan, heat the oil and add the garlic.
Be careful that the garlic does not get brown.
Add shrimp and saute together for about 2 to 4 minutes (depends on the size of your pan).
Add pepper, Creole seasoning, lemon juice, vermouth and salt to taste. Simmer for 2 minutes or until shrimp are cooked.
Serve with crusty French bread or hard rolls.
You can use shrimp peeled first or cook them in the shell and peel later.
Cooking them in the shell, I think, is more fun.
You need to suck the juice out of the shell first, then peel the shrimp, then dip in the sauce again and eat.
Use the bread for dipping.
Wunderbar!

title: skillet lasagna(lite choices)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Divide pizza dough into 4 equal pieces (frozen dough).
Shape each into round with palm of hand.
Place on cornmeal sheet.
Rub olive oil over each; sprinkle with basil. Arrange tomato slices evenly over Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes; serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in large baking dish.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and pour into the baking dish.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: elbow macaroni with cheese and bread crumbs
directions: Bring salted water to a boil and add macaroni.
Cook 8 to 11 minutes and drain. Grate the cheese and set aside.
In a frying pan, melt the margarine or butter. Add bread crumbs and roast until browned.

title: shirley adams' fresh russian tea
directions: Heat water, sugar, and cloves until sugar is dissolved.
On low heat, add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, but do not boil. Serve hot.	Store leftovers in refrigerator or you may freeze.

title: joyce's scratch pancakes
directions: Mix together and cook on hot griddle.
Makes plenty for the whole family or company.
Great when all the kids come home.

title: texas caviar
directions: In a large bowl, mix together onion, green bell pepper, green onions, jalapeno peppers, garlic, cherry tomatoes, Zesty Italian dressing, black beans, black-eyed peas and coriander. Cover and chill in the refrigerator approximately 2 hours. Toss with desired amount of fresh cilantro to serve. Dip with your favorite tortillas.

title: strawberry bonbons
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, coconut, 1/3 cup gelatin, almond extract and enough red food coloring to tint mixture a strawberry shade.
Chill until firm enough to handle.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and refrigerate. Beat the eggs, powdered sugar and oleo for 15 minutes. Spread over graham cracker crust.
Cover with the bananas. Spread the pineapple over top and cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with the nuts, coconut and cherries. Refrigerate 48 hours.

title: quick cinnamon twists
directions: Blend cinnamon, sugar and nuts together.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then in cinnamon mixture.
Twist and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for 8 minutes.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mayonnaise is essentially an egg yolk and oil sauce.
The ratio of egg yolks to oil is generally as follows:

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat. Saute garlic, onion and bell pepper in oil until tender, but not brown.
Combine all other ingredients with sauteed vegetables and shape into a loaf pan.
Cook in oven until brown, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: purple cow popsicles
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Pour into popsicle molds and freeze at 0° or colder for 3 hours or more.
Hold molds under warm water for a few seconds to loosen popsicles.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.
Use about 1/3 cup mix per 8 ounce cup boiling water.

title: curried baked cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets and cook with salt.
Drain well.
In 2-quart casserole, stir together soup, cheese, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Add cauliflower and mix well.
Toss bread crumbs in melted margarine; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: alta's zucchini spice cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn cheese chili pie
directions: Melt butter in a large baking dish.
Mix well the other ingredients and pour into baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until pie is firm when pressed in center.
The corn meal comes to top and forms a thin crust.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate picnic cake
directions: Combine margarine, shortening, cocoa and water in small saucepan.
Bring
to
a
rapid boil and pour over flour, sugar and salt
which
have been sifted into a large bowl.
Mix well and add buttermilk to which soda has been added.
Blend well; add slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
About
minutes
before cake is done, start to make frosting.

title: crunchy crust french toast
directions: Blend together 1 egg, milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix coconut and corn flakes together and put in a pie plate.
Dip 4 slices of bread in egg mixture, then coat with cereal and coconut.
Heat margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Brown toast slices until golden brown on both sides.
Serve hot with maple syrup or honey.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Combine first 11 ingredients.
Turn batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle on top of loaves.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: parish house chow chow relish
directions: Sprinkle tomatoes, onions and red peppers with salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Remove to wire racks; cool completely. Yields 2 loaves.

title: mom olson's russian salad dressing
directions: Buzz all ingredients in a blender or mix well with a wire whisk.
Keep refrigerated and shake well before using.
Makes 1 pint.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend until all ingredients are moistened.
Mix on medium speed for 1 minute or until batter is smooth.
Pour batter into 2 prepared (greased and floured) pans, 1/2 full.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburger and onion mix together.
Drain off fat.
Then add enough catsup to make sloppy.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons mustard and mix.
Now we are ready for buns.
Put mix on bun, top with cheese. Place bun top on and enjoy.

title: pepper turkey loaf
directions: Combine turkey with remaining ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
This is a great low-fat meat loaf.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Cook apples until tender.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar and baking powder with melted butter.
Cut together as for pastry. Spread half of crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with dried apples and sugar and cinnamon mixture that has been heated until sugar dissolves.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put spices and red hots in basket of percolator. Add liquid and perk for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Place 3 tortillas in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Spread half of meat on top and layer with 1/2 can beans, then 1/2 of sliced cheese.
Add another layer of tortillas and repeat layers.
Place remaining 3 tortillas on top.
Mix cream of chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Pour over top of tortillas.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: spice bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
In mixing, make a hole in the mixture and add the other ingredients (already mixed).
Mix well (no mixer).
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: barbecued bologna
directions: Cook onion in butter in saucepan until tender; add chili sauce,
vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, celery salt and
mustard.
Cook
uncovered
until thick.
Cut bread into 13 crosswise
slices,	almost	through
to
bottom crust; place on large
piece of aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Spread 1 tablespoon chili sauce mixture
in	each cut.
Turn loaf of bread on the side.
Insert 1
folded
slice
of
bologna	into each cut, folded edge to the	outside.
Loaf bends into round crown shape as it is
filled.
Spread
remaining
chili
sauce mixture over loaf; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cup foil around lower part of foil to form
container.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Lift crown to serving
plate.
Snip
slices
apart
with scissors to serve. Yield: 6 to 12 servings.

title: southern fried quail
directions: Spread quail open and wipe dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and dredge in flour.
Fill a deep, heavy skillet half full of salad oil; heat to 350°.
Cook quail in hot oil 5 minutes; cover and continue cooking until golden brown, turning once.
Drain well.
Serve birds on a hot platter and garnish with lemon slices and parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate mint creams
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat brown sugar, margarine or butter and water over medium heat just until melted, stirring constantly. Add chocolate pieces.
Heat just until chocolate is melted, stirring constantly.
Then transfer mixture to a large mixing bowl and let cool for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scallops florentine
directions: Thaw scallops, if frozen. Cut any large scallops in half. Cook spinach, drain well and keep warm.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix well with hands.
Press into 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Beat eggs; add 1/2 cup brown sugar, syrup, pecans, melted margarine, vanilla and salt.
Mix and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: herb tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes and slice thick.
Mix all ingredients.
Marinate tomatoes overnight.
To serve:
Arrange tomatoes on a serving plate and spoon a small amount of marinade over them.

title: tuna hot dish
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: fruit compote
directions: Arrange in 3-quart Pyrex dish in order given.
Rinse cherry can with 1/2 cup water and add to casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. May be served hot or cold.

title: peanut bars
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Beat in sugar.
Add dry ingredients and mix lightly.
Add water.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: christmas cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and spices together 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar, gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, honey, almonds, raisins and figs.
Mix well.
Add flour alternately with water.
Beat well.
Bake in greased pan about 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: low-fat chili dip
directions: In medium saucepan, stir ingredients together, using medium heat and stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Serve with Mr. Phipps low-fat tortilla chips.
Can also be used as a sauce for a taco salad.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together the first 5 ingredients. Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Layer chicken on top; salt and pepper.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is done and golden brown.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruits.
Add coconut and nuts.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown burger, onion and green pepper; drain the grease.
Add 1/2 jar of Ragu and spread in casserole dish.
Add a layer of cheese, then a layer of pepperoni and sauce.
Repeat once.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jill's caramel corn
directions: Mix and boil first 4 ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes; do not stir.
Remove from fire and stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda. Pour mixture over 5 quarts of popped corn.
Do not stir in!
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Put back in oven and repeat every 15 minutes until baked for 1 hour.
If peanuts are desired, add after the first 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken or beef
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet.
Simmer for about 25 minutes or until tender.
Salt to taste.

title: pizza fruit platter(origin: unknown)
directions: Combine 1/2 package dry cake mix, water, eggs, butter and brown sugar in mixing bowl. Mix thoroughly. Blend in remaining mix. Fold in nuts.
Divide batter evenly in two.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate morsels and butter together.
Let cool slightly.
Pour this over marshmallows and pecans. Roll into log. Chill and slice or pour into pan.
Let set 1/2 hour and cut into squares.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil. Generously grease foil with butter, then line cookie sheet with soda crackers.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add vegetables and crabmeat; mix well.
Serve on lettuce.

title: easy filled date drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Drop with a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of date or raisin filling on each cookie after making a depression with a teaspoon or knife.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with a wire whisk for 1 minute or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: canned cole slaw
directions: Mix all together and let stand overnight.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Do not cook.
Makes 12 quarts.

title: orange coconut salad
directions: Peel and cut oranges in bite size pieces, removing seeds as you go.
Sprinkle with 1/3 to 1/2 cup sugar, depending on sweetness of oranges. Add 2/3 cup shredded coconut.
Mix well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Blend well.
Add spices and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased or foil-lined loaf pan at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until done.
Cool on rack.

title: angel delight
directions: Break cake into small pieces and layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine condensed milk with cream cheese and pour over cake pieces evenly.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and top with pie filling.
Lip smacking good!!!

title: meat balls
directions: Soak bread in water 2 to 3 minutes.
Squeeze out moisture. Combine soaked bread with remaining ingredients.
Mix well and form into balls and brown in oil.
Add to spaghetti sauce and cook 30 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add milk and butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Mixture should look like heavy cream.
Add more milk, if necessary.
Fill buttered muffin pans to 1/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes more or until done.
Makes 8 to 12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first.
Then add eggs, wesson oil and vanilla. Grease
and flour pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: ham bone and pea soup
directions: In a large soup pot cover ham bone, peas and onion with water. Boil over medium heat until ham is soft and falls off the bone. Remove bone and ham.
Cut ham into small pieces and return to pot. Add Potatoes, chicken bouillon, garlic powder, celery, carrots, black pepper, salt and bay leaf.
Cook until peas, potatoes, carrots and celery are tender.
Serve with hard rolls for dunking.

title: quick strawberry sauce(lo-cal)
directions: Blend reserved juice and cornstarch in small saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in strawberries.
Cool completely.
(Use to serve over low-fat frozen yogurt
or ice milk.) Calories 7 per tablespoon, cholesterol 0 and sodium 0.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and set aside.

title: raisin squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and remaining ingredients.
Be sure to cool raisins and liquid before mixing. Bake on greased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 375°.
Frost immediately with white powdered sugar frosting.

title: goof balls
directions: Melt in a double boiler.
Drop in balls (one at a time).
Lift out with fork and lay on wax paper to cool.

title: touch down stew
directions: Spread baking dish with 1 can cream of mushroom soup (undiluted).
Spread stew meat over that.
Sprinkle 1 envelope dried onion soup mix.
Add 1/2 can water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon custard pudding cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to mixing bowl along with milk and lemon peel.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice.

title: crab meat pizza
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chili sauce and crabmeat until smooth.
Spread on round glass pizza dish (spread out like pizza crust).
Pour Heinz chili sauce over first layer.
Well drain the crabmeat; do not rinse.
Use paper towels to remove excess liquid.
Spread crabmeat over the other layers.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Cook the broccoli in salted water as directed.
Drain and arrange in baking pan. Simmer chicken until tender.
Drain and arrange on top of broccoli.
Mix next 4 ingredients (mayo, lemon, curry powder and chicken soup).
Pour on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Top with bread crumbs mixed with melted butter. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: soft taco bake
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add taco seasoning mix and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Add desired cheese; mix well. Place 2 flour tortillas on bottom of an 8 inch square baking dish. Layer 1/4 of the meat mixture over tortillas. Repeat layers 3 times. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 6 servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
After cool, frost with Peanut Butter Fudge Frosting; yummy!

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 2 hours in open pot.
You can cook 3 hours on low heat.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion and pepper together.
Pour 3/4 cup sugar over all.
Mix 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and remaining ingredients together in pan; bring to boil.
Pour over slaw and cover. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: oat-carrot cake
directions: Generously grease 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Coat pan with nuts.

title: beer cheese soup(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Put 5 cups of milk in large pot.
Hold 1 cup to mix with cornstarch.
Add Worcestershire and Tabasco and stir.
Fry bacon and remove from pan.
In drippings, saute onion until wilted.
Add chicken base and continue to cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add these ingredients to milk.
When milk begins to steam, mix cornstarch with reserved milk.
Add to milk mixture, stirring frequently. When thickened, add Cheez Whiz, stirring constantly.
Stir in beer.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, water and sugar; heat on medium-high until thick.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Allow to cool about 15 minutes.
Arrange strawberries in pie shell.
Pour mixture into pie shell; let stand about 30 minutes.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook ham hock 2 to 3 hours for rich broth, clean meat from bone and cut into small pieces.
Add cheese and broccoli.
Stir in half and half to thin to nice consistency.
Season to taste.

title: doves in wine
directions: Wash
doves
good
in cold water; drain well.
Pat dry. Split down middle.
Mix together flour, salt, pepper, paprika and basil.
Dredge doves in flour mixture.
Put melted butter and garlic
in	heavy
Dutch oven or skillet, covered.	Brown doves over
medium-high
heat.
Pour
bouillon
and wine over doves, cover.
Simmer, stirring frequently, for about an hour. Add mushrooms
and
orange
juice;
simmer
6 minutes longer. Thicken pan juice with a little flour.
Serve hot.

title: spiced cranberry cider
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil.
Then simmer for 20-30 minutes.
Drink & enjoy.

title: pineapple banana congealed salad
directions: Dissolve the 2 boxes of
Jello in the boiling water.
Add cold water.
Cool, but do not allow to set.
Once cooled, add pineapple, bananas, marshmallows, and lemon juice.	Place in refrigerator and allow to partially congeal.
Pour into 11 inch x 14 inch glass dish.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients.
Blend 30 seconds.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, as directed on package, until barely tender. Place in 1-quart casserole.
Top with soup, then cheese.
Toss pieces of bread with melted butter.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jamboree peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sift together flour, 1 cup of sugar, salt and baking powder and blend with milk.
Pour mixture over melted margarine.
Spread peaches over this and sprinkle with other cup of sugar mixed with cinnamon.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix apples, fruit cocktail, coconut and sliced pineapple.

title: cheesy pita pizza
directions: Lightly brush bread with 1 tablespoon of the dressing; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Brush bread half with half of the remaining dressing.
Top with processed cheese and desired pizza toppings. Drizzle with remaining dressing.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese has begun to melt.
Cut into 6 wedges.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. In smaller bowl mix together milk, egg and oil.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture.
Stir only enough to mix.
Fill greased baking pan half full.
Bake at 425 degrees about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.
For muffins baking time is 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ripe cuke pickle relish
directions: Grind together cukes, onions and peppers.
Let stand overnight with 1/2 cup salt.
Drain in the morning and add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes and can.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: company coffee bars
directions: Sprinkle 1 3/4 cups crumbs in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt chips and oleo in saucepan on low heat.
Stir in powdered sugar. Beat egg yolks; stir into chocolate mixture.
Beat whites until stiff.
Fold into chocolate well.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with pecans.
Freeze solid.
Soften ice cream; spread over chocolate layer.
Top with 3/4 cup crumbs.
Cover with foil.
Freeze solid. Serves 16 to 20.
Will keep frozen for 3 months.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice unpeeled cucumbers 1/16-inch thick.
Finely chop pepper and onion and combine with cucumbers in a bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and celery seed and let stand one hour or longer.
Combine sugar and vinegar and add to the cucumber mixture.
Stir well. Cover and refrigerate at least one day.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add gradually to mixture and beat well.
Add vanilla and cinnamon; beat well.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in greased flat pan at 350° for 55 minutes. Suitable for freezing.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook chop meat and drain.
Add taco mix, tomato sauce and 1 cup water.
Simmer until reduced.
Put aside.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add meat mixture.
Serve warm.

title: oohey-gooey cake
directions: Blend together cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Mix well. Press evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Then blend together 2 eggs, cream cheese and the powdered sugar. Mix well and pour evenly on top of cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Wrap 1 water chestnut with 1 piece of bacon; close with a toothpick.
Heat sauce and spoon over water chestnuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Halfway through, spoon sauce over water chestnuts again.

title: harold's men's day biscuits
directions: Mix shortening in flour; add buttermilk, then mix well.
Pour dough on floured surface and knead well.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Bake at 500° until done.
Yields 50 to 60 biscuits.

title: pasta with zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into thin rounds and fry lightly in oil.
Do not overcook.
Put aside and keep warm.
Cook pasta according to directions. Drain pasta and return to pan.

Add Mozzarella cheese and stir quickly so that the hot pasta starts to melt the cheese. Now add the eggs and zucchini, stirring quickly to set the eggs. Add Parmesan cheese and pepper to taste. Stir thoroughly and serve at once.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust: Mix 1 stick margarine (melted) and graham cracker crumbs together. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach salad with strawberries and pecans
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; drizzle with poppy seed dressing. Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Combine oats, sugar and flour; cut in butter until consistency of crumbs. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mexican hat
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Put tortillas in dish, then some meat mixture, beans and cheese. Repeat as many layers as desired.
Pour taco sauce over all this, then more cheese.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: malissa's lemon chicken sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, water and lemon peel in saucepan. Add butter, lemon juice and food color.
Cook over low heat until smooth, beating occasionally with wire whisk.
To be served over fried chicken breasts/thighs (boneless) and rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dorothy's spaghetti sauce
directions: Scald, peel and chop tomatoes.
Chop green bell pepper, hot pepper and onion.
Add to tomatoes.
Put in 2-quart saucepan. Cook until pepper and onion are tender.
Add sugar, thyme, salt and pepper and lemon juice.
Cook about 10 minutes more.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: greek-style chicken
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking
dish with 2 tablespoons of olive oil (not in recipe).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Spread half of parsley on bottom of pan.
Arrange chicken on parsley, season to taste with salt and pepper.
Squeeze lemon over chicken.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight before using.
Serve with chips or pretzels.

title: texas sheet bars
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil.
Then mix eggs, sugar, flour, soda, salt and sour cream.
Then add cocoa mixture. Spread onto 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Top with icing.

title: bourbon balls
directions: First Day:
Soak the nuts in bourbon overnight in refrigerator (or longer).

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Spread 9-inch pie plate with mayonnaise.
Make sure potato slices are dry; use paper towels if needed.
Overlap slices of potatoes until one layer is arranged on top of mayonnaise-brushed pie plate.
Spread again lavishly with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Sprinkle with pepper, if desired.
Repeat same layering again until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil.
Continue baking until potatoes are tender, approximately another 30 minutes.
Invert onto plate and serve.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast and
sugar
in
warm
water.
Add flour. Mix until well blended.
Let
set
in
a warm place overnight. Next morning, add 1/2
cup
flour and carefully stir (with 1/2 cup water) to the mixture.
Ready to use by evening.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Spread
thin	over loaf bread and cut into strips.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Boil macaroni in salt water.
Cook ground meat, onions, salt, garlic and pepper together.
Add cream of chicken and mushroom soups, sour cream, pimento and macaroni.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini crab cakes
directions: Mix together and form patties.
Fry in oil or butter until golden brown.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Note: Betty Powers adds curry powder to taste.

title: linda twelves' barbecued shrimp
directions: Mix and melt all ingredients except shrimp.
Simmer mix for 15 to 20 minutes to get flavors up.
Add unpeeled shrimp.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Check frequently.
Do not overcook.
Serve with baked French bread to sop up juice.

title: no fail pastry
directions: Mix shortening, salt and boiling water.
Add flour after shortening mixture is whipped.
Mix until dough is formed. Refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.
Great for pies.

title: modena mushroom salad
directions: Wash mushrooms, lettuce and carrot; set on cotton dish towel to dry.
Break garlic and rub on inside of 1-quart resealable container (Mason jar or plastic).
Add olive oil, vinegar, oregano, basil, remainder of garlic and mushrooms.
Prepare in the morning and leave out during the day, upending periodically to mix.
tags: Filippo Berio extra virgin olive oil

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Reserve liquid from green beans.
Heat bean liquid, cider vinegar, and sugar until dissolved.
Mix liquid with beans.
Add sliced red onion.
Toss to combine.
Chill salad.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix turkey, grapes and nuts together.
Add Kraft salad dressing.
Put on lettuce leaf and garnish with tomato and serve. Makes one or two servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: cheesy beef nachos
directions: Brown meat; drain. Stir in salsa; simmer for 2 minutes. Arrange chips on microwavable dinner plate. Top with meat mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted, rotating plate every minute. Top with toppings as desired.

title: chicken saute(low-fat)
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Make seasoned flour:
Add onion flakes, parsley flakes and pepper to flour and mix.
Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
Get as much flour as you can to stay on chicken.

title: tangy lamb chops veronique
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow bowl; stir.
Trim fat from chops.
Combine mustard and vinegar; brush mustard mixture over chops.
Dredge chops in bread crumb mixture.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with spray over medium heat until hot.
Add chops, cover and cook 4 minutes on each side.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness. Transfer chops to platter and sprinkle with grapes.

title: lucky chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cool to room temperature. Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in vanilla and chocolate.

title: sweet potato cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, sweet potato, onion and bell pepper in a bowl; toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Add cabbage mix; cover and chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: layered garden pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Stir together macaroni, onions and 2 tablespoons of bacon bits in medium bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, cheese, sugar and garlic powder.
In a 3 1/2-quart salad bowl, layer salad greens, macaroni mixture, zucchini or cucumber, broccoli and tomatoes.
Pour dressing evenly over top.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons bacon bits just before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sugar and raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with the cream.
Add raisins. Mix by hand thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Beat 1 egg and 1 tablespoon cream together.
Brush on cookies.
Sprinkle with plain or colored sugar.
Bake at 325° for about 8 or 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, Jell-O and sugar together real well.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Bring to boil.
Put in pie crust.
Put strawberries on top.
Top with whipped cream.

title: german spinat-kasetortchen(spinach and cheese pie)
directions: Stir flour and salt into a large bowl; cut in butter until mixture is fine crumbs.
Then add water, a little at a time, until dough is moist enough to form a soft ball.
Chill.
Roll out dough; place in a 12-inch quiche pan.
Prick with a fork.
Line with foil and fill with dry beans to hold dough in place.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Remove beans and foil. Return crust to oven.
Bake until golden brown.
Cool.

title: spiced prune cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in prunes.
Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add to creamed mixture in 3 portions, alternately with sour milk in 2 portions.
Turn into greased shallow pan about 13 x 9-inch. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Combine into a pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes. Blend melted butter and flour together and add to corn.
Mix well and remove from heat.
Serves 8.

title: sweet 'n sour hot dogs
directions: In crock-pot put the ingredients.
Turn on low.
Simmer until ready.
Longer allowed to sit, spicier it is!

title: comfits(circa 1800)
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Drop dough into hot shortening and fry quickly until golden on all sides.
Drain on towels.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix brownie mix.
Spread in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Pour chocolate syrup over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in the boiling water.
Beat eggs, cake mix, oil and jello mixture well.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Have ready the powdered sugar and lemon juice, mixed together.
Be sure to mix through the lumps.
Prick top of hot cake with fork all over and pour lemon-sugar over top.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
Mix pudding.
Soften cream cheese and pineapple.
Spread on cake; top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: ribbon fudge parfait
directions: In saucepan, combine pudding mix (dry) and instant coffee; slowly stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: chocolate cake delight
directions: Prepare
and
bake
cake mix according to directions on box. Cool;
break
into	bite
size
pieces.
Prepare vanilla pudding according
to directions on box.
Break chilled candy bars while still
in wrappers.
Spread 1/3 of candy pieces on the bottom
of a large serving bowl.
Follow with 1/3 of cake pieces,
pudding and whipped cream.	Continue until all ingredients are
used up. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Scoop and serve.

title: light and luscious pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Combine cake mix, pineapple juice, water and egg whites in a large mixing bowl.
Blend with mixer on low speed 30 seconds. Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Divide batter between pans.
Bake 29 to 32 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: chili-velveeta dip
directions: Cook and drain beef.
Combine rest of ingredients and microwave until cheese is melted and dip is thoroughly heated through.
Stir to blend.
Adjust garlic and chili powders to taste.
This may be kept warm in a chafing dish.
Serve with tortilla chips or dippers of your choice.
Enjoy!
Ole!

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Place in a Pam-sprayed pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm, topping with catsup of your liking.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until thickened, then add the rest of the ingredients.

title: coffee ring
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water; add 1 cup flour and beat until smooth.
Add oil and eggs and remaining flour and salt. Beat until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and roll on lightly floured board into approximately a 9 x 18-inch oblong.
Spread oleo on the dough sparingly; sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nuts and raisins, if desired.
Roll up and shape into a circle on a greased cookie sheet.
Cut at 2-inch intervals almost through dough.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool and spread with icing.

title: fudge upside-down cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and milk.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Place cake mixture in buttered and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts.

title: ambrosia trifle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl; beat at low speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes or until thickened.
Spoon one-third of pudding into a 3-quart trifle bowl.
Cut coconut cake in half lengthwise.
Cut cake halves crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange one-third of cake slices in a single layer over pudding.

Arrange one-third of Mandarin orange segments over cake. Arrange half of remaining cake slices over orange segments. Cover cake with half of remaining pudding; top with remaining cake slices and half of remaining orange segments.
Top with remaining pudding and orange segments.
Mound whipped topping over trifle. Garnish with shredded coconut and stemmed maraschino cherries. Cover and chill several hours.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice as you normally would.
Heat oil and scramble eggs over low heat.
While eggs are cooking, cut them into small pieces. Add shrimp; stir.
Add salt, pepper and rice.
Stir.
Cook over low heat.
Mix in soy sauce and stir very well.
Then mix in onions. Be sure to add ingredients in this order.
Cook until warm.
Serves 4.

title: tomato salad
directions: Cut tomatoes and peppers into bite sized pieces.
Thinly slice red onion.
Add Good Seasons dressing (tastes best when using Jersey tomatoes from your own garden!).

title: squash casserole
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil and cook 5 minutes. Mix together the eggs and crackers.
Mix liquids with eggs and cracker crumbs.
Mix into squash. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Season to taste.

title: divinity candy
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, 1/4 teaspoon and 1/2 cup water.
Cook to hard ball stage (260° on candy thermometer), stirring only until sugar dissolves.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Gradually pour syrup over egg whites, beating at high speed on electric mixer.
Add vanilla and beat until candy holds its shape, 4 to 5 minutes.
Quickly drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 40 pieces.

title: alphabet salad
directions: Cook and cool
macaroni.
Drain juice from both cans of fruit. Add to
the
juice: sugar, eggs and flour.
Cook until thickened. Let cool.	Mix macaroni, fruit and sauce together. Let set overnight.	Stir in Cool Whip.

title: buns
directions: Scald milk and cream and cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix all ingredients, add flour to make a soft dough. Knead.
Form into a ball and place into a greased bowl.
Let rise until light, about 1 hour.
Punch down and let rest 5 minutes. Form into buns the size for a hamburger.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until light.
Bake in a 425° oven, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Boil beans 15 minutes.
Blend in olive oil, garlic, tomato paste, salt, basil and oregano.
Continue boiling until beans are tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Add more water as needed.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Add Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Serve hot.

title: american style lasagne
directions: Brown beef, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Add tomato sauce, seasonings and onion.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Cook noodles. In a large casserole, alternate layers of meat sauce, noodles, cheese and cottage cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: holiday loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: heavenly hash bars
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows and nuts in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.
In a small saucepan, melt chips and peanut butter over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth. Pour over marshmallows and nuts.
Let stand 8 to 10 minutes. Gently stir to coat marshmallows.
Refrigerate until set. Cut into bars.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package of Jell-O with 3/4 cup water.
Add half the pineapple, half the bananas and half the berries.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until thickened.
Spread sour cream over this. Mix remaining ingredients as previously stated and pour over top. Let set.

title: chocolate nut drop cookies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add condensed milk; cook until thick.
Add nuts (walnuts or pecans) and vanilla.
Let cool.
Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: black bean dip
directions: Drain black beans. Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan. Chop onion finely with stems and mix into black beans. Spread sour cream over top of bean mixture; you may use as much or as little sour cream as you like. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cover with shredded cheese and heat until melted. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: caper-saffron mayonnaise
directions: Scrape top 3/4 of the corn kernels off cob into a bowl. Spread them out onto a piece of cheesecloth that has been stretched over a frame.
Place in the sun to dry.
Turn four times a day until all moisture has been evaporated and the kernels are very hard.
Store in a bag or in a covered ceramic jar in a dry place.

title: chop chop salad
directions: Mix cauliflower, broccoli, carrots and onions in a large bowl. In another container mix sour cream, Miracle Whip, garlic salt and seasoning salts together.
Mix well and add to vegetables. Mix well and chill.

title: philly cheesecake brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Beat cream cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth. Add sugar, mixing until blended. Add egg and vanilla; mix until blended. Pour cream cheese mixture over brownie mixture. Cut through batter with knife several times for marbled effect. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cream cheese mixture is lightly browned. Cool. Cut into squares (about 24 squares). Prep time: 20 minutes. Baking time: 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Divide batter into two well-greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Remove from pans.
This freezes well.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Place 3 slices buttered bread in a greased casserole.
Cover with 1 cup cheese.
Add remaining bread and top with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
(Beat enough to make fluffy.)
Pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand 1 hour or more (overnight is better).
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender; blend until smooth (about 30 seconds).
Makes approximately 6 cups.

title: overnight lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and water. Blend well.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, broccoli, cauliflower, bacon and cheese on top in large bowl.
Spread mixture of Miracle Whip and sugar over top, sealing to edge.
Chill, tightly covered, for 6 hours to overnight.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add the moist mixture to the dry ingredients all at once.
Stir quickly until just mixed.
Gently fold blueberries into batter.
Generously grease a muffin pan and fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion; brown with meat about 1 minute.
Add soups, sauces and chilies.
Layer in an ungreased casserole dish 1/2 package Doritos.
Pour 1/2 meat sauce over Doritos.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over sauce.
Add another layer of Doritos, then sauce, then cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place prepared chicken in bottom of rectangular baking dish.
Mix together the sour cream, soup, celery and onion; spoon over chicken.
Carefully spread until even.
Prepare box of stuffing as directed on box, adding 1/4 cup water and omitting butter.
Let stuffing stand 2 to 3 minutes, then spoon over sour cream mixture, spreading evenly.
Bake for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grandma's tea cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in extract; cover and chill 1 hour.
Roll dough on a floured surface.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges turn brown.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape dough into balls and roll in sugar (optional).
DO NOT FLATTEN COOKIES.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetables and mix well.
Add to vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Will keep well for 2 weeks or more.

title: easy hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook meat, onion, and pepper until lightly browned.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, and garlic salt.
Remove from heat. Cook noodles, drain.

title: hot fudge ice cream topping
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a double boiler. Add sugar and boiling water. Allow to boil 5 minutes or so.

title: tasty tuna casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in onion.
Place remaining ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: two-step minestrone
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, cover with water and simmer 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains per serving: 61 mg. calcium and 161 calories.

title: tiramisu toffee trifle pie
directions: Stir together coffee granules and water.
Cool.
Cut the cake into 14 slices.
Cut each slice diagonally.
Place triangles up the side and on the bottom of a 9-inch deep dish pie pan.
Drizzle coffee mix over cake slices.
Beat cheese, sugar and chocolate syrup together until smooth.
Add 2 1/2 cups whipped topping and beat until smooth.
Spread cheese mixture over cake.
Dollop remaining whipped topping around the edge.
Sprinkle with candy crumbs.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: amish pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into first 3 ingredients, set aside.
Mix last 2 ingredients well and add to flour mixture.
If this seems too wet to work with, refrigerate until stiff.
Makes 3 small or 2 large shells.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into both sides of steak.
Preheat electric skillet to 360°.
Add 2 tablespoons shortening.
Add onions and saute until golden brown.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: maple pudding cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. Add milk and vanilla. Stir only enough to mix. Pour into greased 8-inch pan. Combine maple syrup, water and butter. Heat just to melt butter. Pour over cake batter. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream. Delicious.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add this to the first mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool pan before turning cake out.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Serve with corn chips.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms for 3 minutes in heated olive oil, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Mix in cloves of garlic, salt, white pepper, thyme, tarragon vinegar, lemon rind, lemon juice and bay leaf.
Put in glass bowl.
Cool.
Serve at room temperature. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cover and cook 10 hours on low; 5 hours on high.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
In large bowl beat eggs slightly and add milk, salt, dry mustard, cheese and sausage.
Add bread last. Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let sit for a few minutes.
Serve and enjoy.
Best when served with hot caramel rolls.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: anne's most requested brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except marshmallows.
Bake in pan with greased bottom only at 350° for 28 minutes.
Top with miniature marshmallows.
Return oven to "off" while preparing icing.

title: light and hot chicken salad(lo-fat)
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet. Add flour and stir over medium heat for 1 minute. Do not brown. Add chicken stock and milk. Using a wire whisk, stir mixture over medium heat until it boils. Add salt, garlic powder and pepper; cook 1 minute more.
Combine the soup mixture with chicken, mayonnaise, onion, celery, egg whites, lemon juice, pimento and water chestnuts.
Place in a shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray. Sprinkle with cheese and nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
It is not necessary to refrigerate overnight. Serves 8.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter glass 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Add apple slices.
Mix remaining ingredients (will be mealy) and crumble over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until hash browns have browned and are tender.

title: bec's shoepeg casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, then crackers crushed on top and melted margarine.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in pan. Stir in hot water gradually. Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear, 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir 1/2 cup of hot mixture gradually into beaten egg yolks. Stir back into hot mixture. Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add lemon juice and butter.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add shrimp, onion, pepper and celery; cook and stir until shrimp are pink. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, hot pepper sauce, thyme and garlic powder; bring to boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: momma's depression days cake(eggless, milkless, butterless)
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, raisins, water, shortening, salt and spices. Bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool completely. Add baking powder, then flour.
Mix well.
Bake in a 325° oven in a heavy baking dish or iron skillet (greased and floured) for 45 to 60 minutes.
Will be heavy textured like fruitcake.
Keeps well in cool place.

title: sour cream green beans
directions: Prepare green beans according to cooking instruction, drain. Saute onion and parsley in margarine.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour mixture over green beans and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: liz's pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Top with a little Parmesan cheese, if you want and serve cold with nice crusty Italian bread or hot breadsticks.
Great for a hot summer evening!

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream, chilies, onion, salt and cheese. Dip tortillas into enchilada sauce.
In ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, overlap 2 tortillas to fit width of pan.
Spread about 2/3 cup of chicken mixture down middle of each tortilla.
Fold and turn seam side down.
Repeat with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes or until cheese melts and enchiladas are heated through.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in a large pot and cover with water. Cook until chicken is tender or until fork can be inserted with ease, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Remove chicken from broth. When cool enough to handle, cut into pieces of desired size or leave whole. Cut tortillas into squares. Drop one at a time into boiling broth seasoned to taste with salt and pepper. As tortillas go under the broth, add more until all are in pot. Simmer 5 minutes. Do not stir. TASTY AND EASY!!!!!

title: sesame seed sticks
directions: Cut butter into flour, mixed with salt and cayenne pepper. Sprinkle ice water over dough and toss with a fork until dough will hold together as for pastry.
Roll dough out on a floured board to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Before removing from pan and while still hot, sprinkle with salt.
May be frozen.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover with buttered breadcrumbs.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese tortellini soup
