directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the stock or broth, tortellini, peas, tomatoes, basil and oregano.
Cover and boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until tortellini are tender.
Has 107 calories.

title: turkey tortellini
directions: Start with a large pot (at least 3-quart).
Bring water in pot to a boil.
To it, add cheese tortellini and cook per instructions on bag.

title: mustard potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until limp.
Stir in flour until smooth; add bouillon.
Cook until bubbly.
Season with salt, pepper and mustard.
Slice potatoes in baking dish; pour mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 375° until crumbs are browned.
Sauce may be made ahead and heated when needed.

title: toffee squares
directions: Mix together and press in a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Melt
large
bag milk chocolate chips and spread on top of cake mixture while still warm.
You can also add 1 tablespoon peanut butter.

title: hopping john
directions: Fry bacon in saucepan until crisp.
Add onion and celery; cook until onion is lightly browned.
Add bay leaf and peas with liquid; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in water and rice; bring to a boil, cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken escabeche
directions: Combine broth, lime juice, chili sauce and Worcestershire and mustard.
Add chicken and onion, turning to coat with liquid. Drain chicken and onion well.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Boil until spins a thread as hard crack.
Put in 1 cup raw peanuts.
Cook until caramel color and hard crack.
Take off heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir until bubbly and foamy and light in color.

title: tuna salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and sprinkle chips on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: Place apple slices in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over apples.
Cover loosely with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes or until apples are tender.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.
Contains about 76 calories per serving.

title: chili
directions: Combine in 6-quart pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: kids' favorite hot dogs
directions: Cut frankfurters lengthwise about 3/4 of the way through. Place one wedge of pickle, cut side down, in each frankfurter. Wrap with a slice of bacon.
Secure with wooden picks, if necessary.
Place on grill over ash covered coals so frankfurters are 3 to 4 inches from heat.
Grill at moderate temperature 8 to 10 minutes, turning frequently.
Spread out sides of buns with an equal amount of peanut butter.
Remove wooden picks from frankfurters.
Serve frankfurters in peanut butter buns.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: tasty cheddar-wurst and beans
directions: In a large skillet over low heat, cook Cheddar-Wurst pieces with onion and pepper for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hot vegetables with herbed walnuts
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add walnuts. Sprinkle with dill.
Stir over moderate heat for about 5 minutes or until walnuts are lightly toasted.
Arrange hot cooked vegetables and herbed walnuts on crisp lettuce on serving platter.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt. Heat dressing.
Serve separately with salad.
Yields 6 servings.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, pecans and margarine.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour this over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: country breakfast
directions: Cook potatoes, green pepper and onion in margarine until lightly browned.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Break the eggs over potato mixture. Cover and cook until eggs are done. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover until cheese is melted.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Stir all ingredients in 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion, drain.
Mix noodles, sausage, soup and water.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brunch toast
directions: Butter 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Into pan, tear bread into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces (each with a little crust).

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add next 4.
Blend.
Fold in apples and walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
I usually put in a Bundt pan.

title: easy chicken a la king
directions: In skillet, saute onion and pepper until onion is transparent. Add chicken and soups (do not dilute).
Bring slowly to a boil. Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add pimentos and green peas. Simmer until green peas are ready.
Serve in patty shells, on toast points, rice or noodles.

title: quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle onion, cheese and bacon in unbaked pie crust.
Beat eggs and other ingredients; pour over bacon and cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: In an oblong pan, arrange chicken and line cheese on top of chicken.
Spread croutons over cheese.
In a bowl, whisk soup and milk together.
Pour over mixture. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°. Serve with salad.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch dish in the microwave.
Mix and pour flour, milk and sugar and add to dish.
Spread blueberries on top.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant, pare, then dice (it's about 4 1/2 cups). Add eggplant to a small amount of boiling salted water to which you have added marjoram; cook, covered, about 10 minutes.
Drain well. Cook onions in 2 Tbsp. of butter until tender, but not brown. Add to eggplant along with parsley.
Combine bread crumbs with 1/4 c. melted butter.
In a greased 8-inch pie plate, arrange a layer of eggplant mixture, then a layer of bread crumbs; repeat.
Pour half and half evenly over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain the sweet potatoes.
Beat all of the ingredients and pour into a greased dish. Sprinkle with the topping.

title: chocolate banana pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in medium microwave bowl on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring until completely melted.
Spread evenly in crust.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes, or until chocolate is firm.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes; beat with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Spoon over bananas in crust; spread with whipped topping.

title: sugar cookies 1
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead dough.
Flour counter. Drop out 1/4 of dough onto floured counter.
Flour rolling pin. Roll dough out 1/4-inch or thinly.
Spray cookie sheet.
Cut out cookies and decorate if desired on sheet. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Put on towel or cooling rack.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: morning glorious muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon. In another bowl, combine carrot, apple, coconut, raisins and nuts. Stir in beaten eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 24 muffins.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and cold water. Add flour; mix well and add pecans.
Chill dough.

title: cranberry - nut bread
directions: Combine the flours, sugar, baking powder and orange rind in a mixing bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool for 5 to 7 minutes before removing from pan.
Turn onto a wire rack and cool thoroughly.
Store in a plastic bag or aluminum foil for at least 1 day before slicing. Serves 15.

title: baked crab casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; add 5 hard cooked egg whites (diced). Pour into a shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: tabouli
directions: Pour boiling water over wheat in a large bowl and let stand for 2 to 3 hours or until water is absorbed.
Mix onion, tomatoes, green pepper and parsley into the wheat.
Mix remaining 9 ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Pour over wheat mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Keeps well for 2 to 3 days.
This refreshing and healthy mix is great with Fritos or tortilla chips.
It's also great when served in pocket bread (pita or Arabic)!
Yields 6 cups.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece into a ball. Mix sugar and cinnamon and roll each ball into the mixture.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and pour into bottom of Bundt pan.
Add some nuts.
Layer, using 1 can of biscuits at a time, butter and nuts. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Fun to eat!
Just pull off some of it with your fingers!

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light in color and thick.
Add vanilla and flour; mix thoroughly.
Fold in potato chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: diane's pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be room temperature.
Cream together eggs, butter, Criso and flavoring.
Mix sugar with butter mixture. Slowly add baking powder and flours, sifted together.
Add milk as needed.
Beat as directed.
Mixture will look like ice cream. Spoon out into Crisco-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabsah(rice with meat)
directions: Parboil meat.
Heat oil in a skillet.
Add onion and cook for 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, cumin and spices as desired. Cook for 10 minutes on reduced temperature, lowest level.
Add 4 cups of broth and rice.
Raise temperature and boil until liquid is dissolved.
Reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes.
Serve rice with meat on top, without broth.

title: never fail white icing
directions: Cook over boiling water; beat until stands in peaks.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Continue beating until thick enough to spread.

title: apple and raisin oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray. Combine apply, raisins, brown sugar and cinnamon in medium bowl. Transfer to prepared pie plate. Bake uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes or until apple begins to soften. Remove from oven. Increase oven temperature to 450°. Whisk eggs, milk, flour and margarine in medium bowl until blended. Pour batter over apple mixture. Bake 15 minutes or until pancake is golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: onion rings
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add eggs and milk.
Blend. Dip onion rings into mixture and deep fry at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain and salt.

title: pretty pears for christmas
directions: Divide juice 1/2 and 1/2 in bowls. Add green coloring to one; add red coloring to other. Darken to your liking. Add pears and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix butter and sugar; mix.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.
Stir in flour small amount at a time.
After all has been added, beat 1 minute at high speed.
Add fruit and nuts with spoon.
Bake at 300° on cookie sheet for about 1 hour.

title: mint punch
directions: Pour all ingredients in bowl and stir.
Garnish as you like.

title: rich chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix chocolate wafer crumbs, butter and sugar.
Put mixture on bottom and 1/2 inch up the sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: date 'n nut cake
directions: Cover chopped dates with 1 cup boiling water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Stir 3 times.
In large bowl, mix sugar, shortening, egg yolks, nuts and vanilla.
Add date mixture and stir well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add beaten egg whites and fold in lightly.
Pour batter into angel food cake pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Let stand in cake pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out and finish cooling.

title: reese's bars
directions: Combine ingredients (except chocolate chips) and mix together well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill. Melt chocolate chips and spread over graham cracker mixture. Chill again.
Cut into bars.

title: little pizzas for teens
directions: Spread party rye bread with pimento cheese.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 250° until cheese melts.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add cream cheese. Stir until dissolved. Cool. Add pineapple, sugar, vanilla and pecans. Stir. Add 7-Up. Stir well and chill until set.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak dried beans in water overnight.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Mix together and let it just come to a boil.
Cool 10 minutes. Add 1 quart sliced strawberries.
Put in cooled baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas in a large mixing bowl; add dry ingredients.
Mix in bowl and then pour into a baking pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Use a greased loaf pan.

title: low cholesterol pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine for 7 minutes; add extracts, milk, flour, salt and baking powder, mixing well.
Add egg substitute, a small amount at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Put alternative layers of broccoli, sharp grated cheese (Cheddar) and sauce in baking dish.
Top with toasted almonds and bake.

title: cornstarch dough
directions: Mix cornstarch, baking soda and water in pan.
Cook on stove over medium heat 4 minutes.
Stir constantly until mashed potato consistency.
Remove from heat.
Cover with damp cloth to cool 1 hour.
Knead on wax paper; roll out with rolling pin.
Cut into shapes and let dry overnight.
Paint; seal with coat of Elmer's glue.
Glue to pin backing or poke hole before drying for necklace.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, milk, sour cream and Eagle Brand with mixer for 1 to 2 minutes until it begins to thicken.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with vanilla wafers.
Place a layer of bananas over wafers and top with pudding mixture.
Chill.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Crush the pretzels.
Mix with melted margarine and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.
When cool, pour in Dream Whip to which sugar and cream cheese have been added. Smooth over pretzels.
Add slightly congealed jello and strawberries.
Refrigerate until completely congealed.

title: broccoli, cheese and chicken casserole
directions: Put torn chicken pieces in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In medium saucepan, combine soup and milk.
Stir until smooth. Sprinkle broccoli over chicken.
Pour soup mix over broccoli. Prepare stuffing according to package directions using water and margarine.
Spread over broccoli mixture.
Cover with foil and cook 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove foil and bake an additional 5 minutes to brown stuffing.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Slice or dice potatoes.
Make sauce of milk, butter, flour and salt.
Add cheese.
Mix together and put in casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon logs
directions: Cut off crust and roll bread flat.
Spread cream cheese mix (cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk) on bread and roll up. Place in freezer for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf(easy meat loaf)
directions: Mix ingredients together (except 1/4 cup ketchup) then form a loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Spread 1/4 cup ketchup on top of meat loaf and bake 15 minutes more.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a shallow baking dish. Arrange chicken tenders in a single layer in the bottom of the dish. Place cheese slices on top of chicken. Mix soup and wine together; pour over cheese and chicken. Sprinkle stuffing on top of the soup; then drizzle with melted butter. Bake 45-55 minutes.

title: easy cheesy kielbasa with beans
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a stockpot over medium-high heat, stirring until meat crumbles and is no longer pink.
Remove from pot and drain.
Brown sausage in stockpot; drain and return to pot. Add ground chuck mixture, tomato soup and next six ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Yield:
12 servings.
Prep:
10 minutes. Cook:
1 hour.

title: easy burrito bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until done, drain.
Grease a 9x13 pan.
Mix beans, bisquick and water.
Spread in dish; layer beef, salsa and cheese.
Bake 350° 30 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar and eggs.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add lemon extract and gently fold in strawberries.
Spoon batter into well-greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: amaretto mousse* * * * *
directions: The Shrimp Salad is family, the Cauliflower and Broccoli is from a T. V. cooking show and the Amaretto Mousse was cut from a magazine.
You could say this is Wisconsin, Iowa and Arkansas.

title: carrots lyonnaise(with onions)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add sliced onions and cook, covered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cut carrots, after paring, into 3 x 1/4-inch julienne strips.
In separate utensil, dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 to 1 cup boiling water. Parboil carrots in chicken bouillon about 8 minutes until barely tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper and broth from carrots gradually to onions, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Add carrots and simmer, uncovered, until carrots are tender (few minutes).
If desired, add a pinch of sugar just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: low calorie fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off of fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Save.
Mix fruits together.
Mix juice with pudding.
Blend well.
Add quickly to fruit and sweetener mix.

title: tangy lemon streusel cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 2 tablespoons cake mix. Beat remaining cake mix, yogurt, oil, water and eggs for 30 seconds and then on high for 2 minutes.
Mix reserved cake mix, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half of batter into pan. Sprinkle with half of walnut mixture. Repeat with remaining batter and nut mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: crusty biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cream of tartar and baking powder.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix in egg and milk, stirring just until moistened.
Knead 10 times on floured surface and pat to desired thickness.
Cut with floured cutter; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
(Also excellent baked in an ungreased frying pan over low heat on charcoal or gas grill.)

title: easy party punch
directions: Dissolve 2 packages of jello in boiling water.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Stir in ice cubes until melted.
Spoon in sherbet. Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and reduce oven to 325°.
Bake for 30 more minutes.
Contains no sugar.
Good to use for diabetics.

title: crab casserole
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Dice half of bread and put in bottom of a large casserole dish.
Combine crabmeat, mayonnaise, celery, green pepper, onion and salt and spread over bread.
Trim crust from remaining bread.
Dice and put over crabmeat mixture.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spoon soup mixture over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour longer.

title: baked fish
directions: Rinse roughy in cold water.
Dip each piece in oil and then in bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and put a tablespoon of tomato sauce on each piece of fish.
Sprinkle oregano on each and place a bay leaf around the fish.
Sprinkle a little oil around the bottom of the pan and cook for about 15 minutes at 350°, more or less, depending on the thickness of fish.

title: boston linked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In the morning, boil until the skins are tender, but not broken.
Mix in all ingredients, except for the pork sausage.
Place mixed vegetables in a crockery casserole and top with the pork sausage.
Place casserole in a pan of water in oven and simmer slowly at 250° for about 6 hours.
They can be eaten in as short a time as 3 hours, but the longer it simmers, the more delicious it becomes.
If it gets too dry, water may be added. Serve hot.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Use a large bowl to mix it in.
Combine shortening and boiling water or milk.
Stir until melted.
In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir, then add cold water.
Put both packages of yeast in lukewarm water and dissolve.
Combine all 3 mixtures in the large bowl.
Stir well.
Add flour.
Will be a little wet. Cover tight and chill overnight.
Shape, let rise and bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: garlic toast
directions: Spread each slice of bread with Mazola, then spread with garlic spread.
Place slices in broiler.
Heat until brown on broil setting for no longer than 1 minute.
Check to make sure broiler pan is not too close to oven burner, or bread slices will burn.
Heat slices a few seconds longer to brown tops of bread slices until they are crunchy.
Serve immediately.
Crusts are best.

title: cheese asparagus puffs
directions: Mix cream cheese and Blue cheese together and set aside.
Cut crust off bread and flatten each piece of bread with a rolling pin.
With a spatula, spread a thin layer of cheese mixture over bread.
Place asparagus on bread and roll.
Cut each bread stick into pieces.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam and arrange pieces in rows.
Brush lightly with melted butter for 5 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Bake at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer until thick, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook noodles.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.

title: lollipops
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Insert a candy thermometer and do not stir once the candy reaches 200°.
Cook the candy to 290° on a clear day and 300° on a humid day.
Remove from heat, add coloring and flavoring; do not stir.
Pour into molds sprayed with vegetable oil.
Insert sticks.
Let cool.
Makes about 20 lollipops.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla and boil for 1 to 2 minutes and pour over peanut butter, oats and cocoa. Mix thoroughly and spoon drop onto wax paper to cool.

title: corned venison
directions: Place all ingredients in a pickle crock or glass jar and add water to make 6 gallons.
Corning should be done at a temperature of about 38°.
If this is not possible, add 1/3 more salt for every 15° increase in temperature.
For example at 83° add 3 more pounds of salt.
Place the meat in the liquid and weight it down with a plate.
Cover and let it stand for 15 days.
On the 5th and 10th days, stir the liquid and turn the meat over.
On the 15th day, remove the meat and store in a cool place.

title: banzita(bulgaria)
directions: Preheat oven to 375F. Grease a 9x13 inch pan. In a small bowl, mix Feta Cheese and four Eggs together. put the first Filo sheet on the bottom of the pan, brush with one tablespoon of melted butter. Repeat with three more Filo Sheets. On the fourth sheet, put half of the egg/cheese mixture. Place another sheet of Filo dough on top, brush with butter and repeat three more sheets. Cover with remaining egg/cheese mixture and four more sheets of Filo dough. Carefully cut squares in pan. Pour any remaining melted butter on top. Combine one egg and Seltzer Soda and pour on top of Banitza. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Take out of oven and sprinkle with cold water. Cover with paper towel and dish towel. Let stand for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar and serve warm.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup of boiling water.
Melt sour cream and ice cream with 1 cup water.
Combine with jello and add fruit. Chill until set.
If you use strawberry jello, you could use strawberries and bananas.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save syrup).
Add water to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling; dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid.
Cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.
Blend fruits; fold into gelatin and chill.
Blend cheese with topping.
Put on top.
Toast pecans in 1 tablespoon butter.
Spread on top.
Chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onion, celery, cheese, mayonnaise, and water chestnuts together.
Bake for 30 minutes a 350 degrees.
Mix crackers and margarine together to make topping.
Top with topping and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Spread in cake pan and pour mushroom soup on hamburger.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat to cook 40 to 45 minutes.
Add evaporated milk and margarine. Stir frequently until thickened.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water; when soft, rub through strainer.
Scald milk; add to potatoes.
Mel butter; add dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed; stir into boiling soup.
Cook 1 minute.
Strain and sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in mixer.
Add pecans. Finish filling ice cream freezer with milk.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Saute bacon in Dutch oven until browned.
Remove and reserve. Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper and saute a few pieces at a time in bacon drippings until well browned on all sides.
Add onions and carrots and saute until lightly browned.
Pour off all fat.
Add garlic.
Sprinkle meat with two tablespoons of flour; toss.
Add wine and bouillon.
Tie parsley, celery and bay leaf together with string.
Add to meat and simmer until fork-tender.

title: cheesy triangles
directions: Put hamburger in bowl and add cayenne and salt.
Divide into 8 portions and flatten each into a triangular shape.
Press cheese portion in center and seal evenly around the cheese.
Beat eggs and spread out bread crumbs on plate.
Dip each triangle into egg, then into bread crumbs coating even.
Put oil in skillet (repeat dipping triangles a second time) and place in skillet browning each side until golden brown.
Can deep fry also.
Drain on paper towels.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and cook on High for 8 minutes. Stir at 4 minutes.
Add butter and cook 2 more minutes.
Now add baking soda and stir.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients to a batter consistency.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Add jello dry to rest of ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: dill dip
directions: Serve with pumpernickel bread or dark rye (better).

title: divinity fudge
directions: Put sugar, water and syrup in heavy pan.
Boil to soft ball stage.
While it is boiling, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla, beating.
Pour half of cooked syrup over egg whites slowly, beating all the time.
Boil remaining syrup to crack stage.
Add to egg mixture, beating all the time again.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: Saute oleo and minced garlic.
Add green pepper and mushrooms. Add shrimp.
Cook about 5 minutes or until shrimp is done.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: Place candy bars and water in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook until candy bars melt. Cool about 20 minutes. Gradually fold whipped topping into cooled chocolate; spoon into pastry shell. Chill 8 hours. Makes 1 9-inch pie.

title: shrimp fritters
directions: Mix egg with all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep fat.
Mixture may be made ahead of time and refrigerated.
Makes a little bit of shrimp go a long way.

title: parisian pudding pie
directions: Combine flour, 3/4 cup pecans, margarine and brown sugar.
Pat in bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Spoon over cooled crust.
Combine vanilla and chocolate pudding mixes with milk; beat until thick.
Spread over second layer.
Cover with 2 cups Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with remaining chopped pecans.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: cheap cocoa cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening, water and eggs. Mix with mixer; add vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add milk; mix.
Add pineapple and bread; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry Jello in large bowl. Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese. Turn into pan or dish. Place mandarin oranges on top of mixture. Mix well with other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, Quaker oats, eggs, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Press into loaf pan and cover with mustard.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top. Bake for 1 hour or until meat is done.
Drain.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: crab biscuit
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Separate all the crescent rolls.
Place crab mixture in each triangle.
Wrap once.
Cut cheese into strips.
Put a strip over biscuit.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 250° oven.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until smooth.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt alternately with milk. Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hungarian cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ground round, onion, egg, rice and garlic powder together. Cut a slice of cabbage at core end; remove core.
Put cabbage in a large pan of boiling water until leaves are soft enough to roll and tuck ends in.
Put mixture on leaf of cabbage; leave only 1-inch on each end (parts cut off save in bowl for later).
Roll and tuck corners in.
Once wrapped, set aside.
You'll have a small head left when leaves get too small.
Cut up remaining cabbage (1/2 inch wide).
Put in a large pot.
Add whole tomatoes (crush) and tomato sauce (don't mix it up).
Lay cabbage rolls on top, cover with water and cook 2 hours.
Two pounds usually makes 24 rolls.

title: fire and ice
directions: Place onions, tomatoes and green pepper in bowl.
In a saucepan bring all remaining ingredients to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
While still hot, pour over vegetables.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Pour chips in dish, then milk.
Cut butter up and add to chips and milk.
Stir.
Microwave on High for four minutes.
Stir often.
If chips are not melted after four minutes, cook a little longer.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator to harden.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine, add sweet potatoes and broccoli, add chicken broth and chicken breast.
Cook 10 minutes, add potatoes (sweet and white) and seasonings.
Cook till chicken is done add milk last.

title: melting moment cookies
directions: In bowl stir together first 3 ingredients.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine until smooth.
Beat in flour mixture and vanilla until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet, flatten with lightly floured fork.
Bake in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: quick beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan, stirring until crumbly.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(No need to brown meat beforehand.)
Bake covered at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: gourd seed
directions: Place cereals, pretzels and peanuts in large pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients; add to the pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: orange raisin muffin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper cups.
Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add combined milk, oil, egg and grated orange peel.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown and wooden toothpick comes out clean. Remove to wire rack.
In small bowl, combine powdered sugar and orange juice.
Drizzle over slightly cooled muffins.

title: raspberry swirl dessert
directions: Combine coconut and margarine; press firmly on bottom and up sides of 8-inch or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
In another container blend raspberries until smooth.
In small saucepan combine raspberries and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Cool to room temperature.
Meanwhile in small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water; let stand 1 minute.
Over low heat, stir until gelatin dissolves; set aside.
In large bowl combine condensed milk, sour cream, liqueur and gelatin; mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill 10 minutes or until mixture mounds slightly. Spread half the gelatin mixture into prepared pan.
Top with half the raspberry mixture in small amounts.
Repeat layers.
With table knife or spatula swirl raspberry mixture through gelatin mixture. Chill 6 hours or until stiff.
Remove sides of spring-form pan. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: caramel nut rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in 1/4 cup of sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons of oleo, egg and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Work in enough flour until dough is easy to handle. Place greased side up in a greased bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or up to 4 to 5 days or continue to complete at once.

title: dreamy creamy pie
directions: With 3 cups milk, mix vanilla pudding in blender.
Pour half in each crust.
Allow to set 5 minutes.
With 3 cups milk, mix chocolate pudding in blender.
Pour half in each crust on top of vanilla pudding.
Allow to set 5 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip. (Use D-Zerta topping to make absolutely sugarless.)
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Chill before serving.

title: clay
directions: Heat water and salt to almost boiling.
Remove from heat and add salad oil and powdered alum.
Cool 5 minutes.
Knead in flour.

title: tupelo catfish gumbo
directions: Cut catfish into 1-inch pieces.
Cook celery, green pepper, onion and garlic in fat until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Combine vegetable mixture, bouillon, tomatoes, okra and seasonings.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add fish.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Remove bay leaf.
Place 1/4 cup rice in each soup bowl; fill with gumbo.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: egg with a hat
directions: With a 2 1/2-inch round cutter, cut out a circle on the slice of bread.
Melt butter in a heavy frying pan.
Put in both pieces of bread.
Cook over moderate heat until they begin to brown. Break an egg into the hole and sprinkle it with salt and pepper. Continue cooking until the bread is brown.
Turn and brown the other side.
Add butter as needed to keep the bread from sticking. Serve with the cut-out piece on top.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Lightly grease pie pan.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower. Drain and mix vegetables, onions, peppers and cheese.
Pour into pie pan.
Beat other ingredients 15 seconds at high speed.
Pour over ingredients in pie pan.

title: foil-baked sole and veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut 4 squares of foil (12-inch squares). Chop scallions; cut carrots and celery into thin slices. Place fish filet in center of each piece of foil, dividing equally.
Sprinkle scallions, carrot and celery on top of each.

title: teriyaki sauce(for 3 to 4 pounds of meat or poultry)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate meat a minimum of 1 hour to overnight.
Sauce keeps well in refrigerator.

title: quick chicken in wine
directions: Place the chicken in a large baking dish with a tight fitting cover.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and distribute the onion over the chicken.
Drizzle the olive oil over all.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover and place in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until the thickest portions of the chicken can be easily pierced with a fork.
Add vinegar and wine; cover again and return to the 350° oven for an additional 20 minutes.
Uncover and continue to bake for 10 minutes or until the top of the chicken turns a delicate brown and the liquid is reduced by half.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms in a large jar and shake well.
Cut stems from mushrooms at base of caps and add caps to marinade.
Marinate, covered, at least 24 hours in refrigerator.
(Best if marinated several days.) To serve, drain.

title: sugar-jam sandwich cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Separate egg yolks and whites.
Whisk yolks, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir in flour, one cup at a time.
Roll out cookie dough and cut round cookies with whiskey glass or something that size.
Take half of the cookies and cut the centers out with something the size of a thimble.
Bake them on an ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 9 minutes.
While cookies are still hot, spread bottom of sandwich cookie with jam of your choice.
Put "ring" cookie, with center cut out, on top of jam. Brush top with egg whites that have been beaten with a fork.
Then sprinkle chopped walnuts on top.
Allow them to cool and enjoy.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat.
Add salt, cocoa and vanilla.
Add flour; beat until smooth and then fold in nuts. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 325°.
While warm, spread with powdered sugar or these may be frosted when cool.

title: skyler's best barbecue sauce
directions: In a blender, combine brown sugar, ketchup, whiskey, vinegar, water and Worcestershire sauce. Season with liquid smoke, mustard, paprika, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce. Blend until smooth. Transfer to a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add garlic salt, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In another bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Cook noodles, according to directions.

title: crumpets
directions: In a large bowl, combine yeast, sugar and water.
Let stand until bubbly (about 15 minutes).
Blend in milk, egg and 1 tablespoon of the butter.
Add flour and salt and beat until smooth.
Cover and let stand in a warm place until almost double (about 45 minutes).

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt margarine in a large pot.
Add flour and stir over medium heat until roux is light brown. (1-2 minutes)
Stir in celery, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender/crisp. (2 - 3 minutes)
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice. Simmer 20 minutes.
While soup is simmering, make 3 cups of rice. Ladle soup into bowls and top each with 1/2 cup of rice.
*I use Minute Rice.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces and place in bowl.
Cook the oil, vinegar and sugar until clear.
Add 1/3 cup Wish-Bone Italian lite dressing.
Toss all with vegetables and refrigerate.

title: german cabbage rolls
directions: Dip cabbage in hot water to soften.
Cut center out and pull leaves apart.
Roll meat into cabbage leaves.
Place cabbage leaves on the bottom of a large roaster or cook in crock-pot.
Add sauerkraut over the cabbage leaves and repeat layers.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Freeze on cookie sheets before serving.

title: bean and rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet and drain off grease.
Add it to the rice and beans.
Stir.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix spices and vinegar, in a bowl, then add olive oil.
Pour over broccoli and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with pimento strips on top or tomatoes for garnish.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Measure flour by sifting.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; stir in.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mama's lane cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease three 9-inch cake pans on the bottom only.

Line the bottoms with wax paper cut to fit. Grease the paper and lightly dust with flour. In large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff. Set aside. In another bowl, cream the butter and sugar. Add the vanilla. Mix well. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt in another bowl. Stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk. Mix well.

Fold in the beaten egg whites. Pour about 2 1/2 cups of batter into each pan. Smooth the tops. Bake for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the center of the layers. Remove from pans immediately. Remove paper and cool completely on rack.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Fry pork chops until brown on each side.
Season to taste. Put into buttered baking dish.
Top each with apple slices. Sprinkle brown sugar over apples.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Add corn bread to broth.
Add onion, eggs, sage, salt and pepper.
Mash very fine and dissolve all bread (use the loaf bread or biscuits to thin or thicken mixture as needed).
Bake until mixture sets at 400°.

title: apple cake(baldwin or courtland apples)
directions: Mix the 5 tablespoons of sugar with the cinnamon.
Set aside. Mix 1 3/4 cups sugar with the oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder; add this to egg mixture along with orange juice.
Beat about 400 strokes.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: In a medium size saucepan.
Mix fruit, honey, sugar and water. Cook on medium-low heat for about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook until fruit is tender and liquid is thickened. More water may be needed.
On a floured surface, roll each biscuit round and as flat as possible.
Place about 2 Tbsp. of fruit mixture on pastry; fold and seal edges with a fork.
Fry in shortening until brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 10 pies.

title: watergate or pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple, pudding, bite size marshmallows and nuts. Blend in Cool Whip.
(Marshmallows can be omitted and is still good.)

title: meatballs oriental
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, minced onion, salt, pepper and milk lightly but thoroughly.
Shape into 12 meatballs.
Melt butter in skillet on medium heat.
Add meatballs and brown on all sides.
Push to one side and add celery and green pepper.
Remove skillet from heat.
Drain bean sprouts and mushrooms, reserving liquids.
Add water to liquids to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Blend cornstarch with a little of the mixture to make a smooth paste, then blend with remaining liquid.
Stir in soy sauce, then pour mixture over meatballs in skillet.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover and simmer until sauce is thickened and clear, about 20 minutes. Add bean sprouts, mushrooms and sliced onions.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pan with Pam.
Drizzle 1/2 cup sauce (or less) bottom of pan.
Mix Ricotta, spinach, salt, oregano, pepper, egg and 1 cup shredded cheese in bowl.
Lay 4 uncooked noodles in pan; cover with half spinach-cheese mixture. Top with 1 cup sauce.
Repeat noodles, remaining spinach-cheese mix and 1 cup sauce.
Lay 4 remaining noodles on top.
Cover with remaining sauce, then Mozzarella.
Pour water around edges. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes, then serve.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in quart jars.
To each jar, add 1 teaspoon dill seed, 1/4 teaspoon alum and 2 cloves garlic.
Heat salt, water and vinegar to boiling.
Pour into jars. Seal.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in fat until tender; add okra, cook until onion is golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings. Allow to simmer until okra is tender and mixture thickens; add water as necessary.
Green pepper and garlic may be added.
Yields 8 servings.

title: e-z cheesy nacho dip
directions: Use microwave 9 x 13-inch dish.
Line dish with thin layer cream cheese.
Spread can turkey chili on top.
Spread then line of medium salsa. Sprinkle shredded cheese.
(For a spicier taste, use sharp cheese.)
Heat in microwave until cheese melts.
Dip with nacho chips.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased (or Pam) pan.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Wipe steak with
damp cloth.
Season.
Salt and pepper. Slice onion over	1/2 of meat (folded).
Spread sauce and fold meat together.
Pin
edges
with
toothpicks.
Sprinkle	with flour on both sides.
Beat meat on both sides until onions are beaten well. Brown
on	each side in butter.
Place in baking dish/pan.
Make gravy
and	pour over meat.
Bake slowly for 1 hour.

title: mesquite chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups with 2 cans of water.
Cook rice according to directions.
Butter bottom of large casserole dish (3-quart).

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour over cleaned chicken parts.
Bake in oven at 400° until done.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Combine juice, sugar and flour.
Heat over low heat until some sugar melts.
Stir in pineapple and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with crackers.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Blend flour and sugar and set aside.
Mix all liquids together after melting oleo.
Stir all together, leaving pecans until last. Stir well.
Pour into large cake pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Take olive oil in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle meat with garlic and pepper.
Cook until meat is browned.
Add beef broth, water, onion soup mix, bay leaf and spices to taste.
Add carrots, potatoes, turnips, onions and barley.
Can add string beans or peas at the very end of cooking.
Bring to boil, then simmer for a couple of hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger, oats, onion, eggs pepper, celery, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Mix in juice or milk.
Place in a loaf pan; and cook in oven at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fudge or penuche
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch heavy aluminum pan.
Cook in a 2-quart heavy saucepan; use a slotted spoon.

title: jan's green noodle-chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender, reserve broth.
Saute peppers, celery and onion in butter.
Add soup, cheese and olives.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Chop chicken into bite size pieces. Reserve 1 1/2 c. chicken broth after cooking noodles and mix with all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13 buttered dish and
bake, covered, at 350 degrees until it bubbles.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and flake.
Combine salmon and egg whites.
Saute green pepper and onion in oil.
Add bread crumbs and toss until vegetables are tender.
Add to salmon.
Mix in lemon juice, rosemary and pepper.
Form into 4 patties.
Spray a nonstick skillet with Pam.
Cook patties 3 to 4 minutes on each side until brown.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Mix well, then add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese puff sandwiches
directions: Break enough eggs for each child and add milk; add some green food coloring and beat.
Cook and eat.
Serve with ham.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla in double boiler.
Beat 1 minute with electric mixer or rotary beater.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly with either beater until mixture forms peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until spreading consistency.
Will frost tops and sides of two 9-inch layers or one 10-inch tube cake.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 4-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat until sugar dissolves (as it begins to bubble) and stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter thoroughly.
Add Rice Krispies; continue to mix until all cereal is well covered.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan lined with waxed paper.
Press mixture into pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together in a double boiler.
Pour over the top, spreading evenly.
Cool until firm; cut into bars.
Yields about 48 (2 x 1-inch) bars.

title: corn flake christmas holly
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Add green food dye until color desired.
Remove from heat.
Add corn flakes cereal. Stir until well coated.
Quickly, using butter spatula or waxed paper, drop corn flakes onto waxed paper.
Shape into wreath and spread teaberries on.

title: grandmom's rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Soak raisins in water until softened.
In a casserole dish, beat milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg at high speed for 2 minutes until foamy.
Add in rice and raisins.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mulled wine
directions: Mix ingredients except for wine.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Add wine.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Do not boil.
Wrap cloves and cinnamon in cheesecloth, gauze or net for easy removal.

To serve 15, triple the recipe, 3 bottles of wine, approximately 1/2 gallon. To serve 30 people, 6 bottles of wine (approximately 1 gallon), 9 cups water, 3 cups sugar, 2 whole lemons, 3 to 4 oranges, 6 to 8 cinnamon sticks and cloves.

title: no bake bread dough and paint
directions: Mix and knead until well blended.
If mixture is too dry, add a drop or two of glue.
If too moist, sprinkle with flour and cornstarch.
After making the desired art project, allow to dry for 24 hours, turning several times.
To paint, use Elmer's glue paint recipe.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Saute onions and garlic with ground meat in skillet.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place 1/2 of batter in well-greased skillet/pan (dusted with meal).
Spread grated cheese over batter. Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake for 5 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 50 to 60 minutes until top is set.

title: dark rich fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add brown sugar, milk, molasses and oleo.
Sift dry ingredients; add flour and fruit.
Line pans with wax paper and grease pans.
Pour batter into pans and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: pecan nut squares
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Spread on greased cookie sheet. Mix egg white and sugar.
Spread on mixture.
Add chopped nuts evenly.
Press in batter lightly.
Bake at 250° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cut while warm.

title: pig pickin' cake(must be refrigerated)
directions: Add all ingredients to mix in order.
Stir until well mixed. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cajun casserole
directions: Wash beans.
Put in a large pot and cover with water and 2 teaspoons salt. Soak overnight.
In the morning, drain and add 2 quarts water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 hours.
Add seasoning packet from bean package and all ingredients except rice. Simmer 30 minutes. Stir in rice and serve hot or freeze to serve later.

title: easy cinnamon fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square baking pan with foil, allowing foil to extend over sides. Butter foil. In bowl, mix sugar, cocoa and cinnamon. In saucepan, heat butter and cream until butter melts (do not boil). Add vanilla. Combine with sugar mixture. Stir in nuts. Pour into prepared pan. Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Use foil to lift out of pan. Cut into 2-inch squares. Diagonally cut each square in half, making triangles. Garnish with whole nuts, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw frozen hash browns.
Mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening together; add eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; blend. Add milk and flour alternately until blended.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May also put in crock-pot on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream and whipping cream.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour or until thickened.
Combine fruit and coconut.
Stir in the sour cream mixture.
Chill, covered, 2 to 24 hours.
Before serving, stir and sprinkle with toasted coconut, if desired.
Makes 12 buffet servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix apples, Cool Whip and nuts.
Let set overnight.
Mix together cranberries (whole berries) and sugar.
Add to apple mixture and serve.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients and store in airtight container.
To make hot cocoa, use 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: tuna stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub skin with oil.
Bake in hot oven about 1 hour or until soft.
Cut each potato in half and scoop out into a bowl, keeping shells intact.
Mash hot potatoes; add butter, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough milk to make potatoes soft and fluffy.
Heap into skins, building up sides and leaving hole for tuna mix.

title: turkey-vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook vegetables according to directions; drain.
Melt margarine in a 2-quart pan.
Add to margarine the onions, celery and thyme leaves.
(Thyme leaves must be crushed.)
Stir until onion is tender.
Add soups and milk; stir until smooth.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. To serve:
Mix 1 cup of boiling water with two teaspoons of mix.

title: chili
directions: Put beans, tomato juice and water in a 6-quart pan.
Bring to a boil.
Put ground beef in skillet and cook until well done and lightly browned.
Stir in Chili-O mix.
Stir ground beef and Chili-O mix into pan with beans and tomato juice.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Thicken with flour and water.

title: polish nut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when cooled.

title: lemon crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine ingredients; mix well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 9 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Cool on pan 1 minute. Remove to wire racks to cool completely. Makes 48 cookies.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, milk, chocolate and salt in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until smooth and mix thickens.
Remove.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Makes 3 cups.

title: luscious butterscotch yams
directions: Wash, peel and cook yams.
Place quartered yams in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven.

title: old fashioned vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat approximately 15 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir 1 cup of hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute, remove from heat.
In a large bowl, add chilled mixture, stirring with a wire whisk to combine.
Freeze according to ice cream maker's directions.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually stir in broth.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add peas.
Chop cooked chicken into pieces.
Add mushroom caps, pimento and soup to chicken mixture.
Heat until bubbling. Pour into casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper, onion and mix with grated carrots.
Mix 1 cup sugar and salt.
Pour over vegetables.
Heat vinegar, oil and 2 tablespoons sugar until sugar dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Pour over all other ingredients and stir well.
Put in glass or stoneware jar only.
Cover and let set for 24 hours.

title: microwave no fuss caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn and peanuts in a large brown paper bag; set aside.
Place brown sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass bowl or casserole dish.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute, until mixture comes to a boil. Microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in baking soda.

title: ham and potato hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix potatoes, ham and cheese.
Add combined milk, Miracle Whip and pepper.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 quart casserole.
Toss crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: ginger cream dressing
directions: Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons pineapple-orange juice in a small saucepan; stir until smooth.
Add remaining pineapple-orange juice, ginger, honey and lemon juice; stir well. Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and transfer to a small bowl.
Cover and chill.
Stir in yogurt just before serving.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup stuffing mix. After draining spinach, mix all ingredients gently. Put into 2-quart casserole.
Top with the 1/2 cup stuffing mix and 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach ricotta pizza
directions: Spread Ricotta cheese on crust, then layer the rest of ingredients over crust, ending with Mozzarella cheese and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Combine brownie mix, yogurt, egg substitute and vanilla in bowl.
Mix well; batter will be very thick.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake for 22 to 24 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan, 32 to 34 minutes in 9 x 9-inch pan and 32 to 34 minutes in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: shrimply divine dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in sour cream and remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving with crackers.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook milk and rice in double boiler until rice is tender (about 1 hour).
In a bowl, beat the eggs.
Add to the rice and milk for the last 5 minutes of cooking. Take mixture off stove.
Add the sugar and vanilla to mixture and stir well.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion, salt and water.
Let stand in glass or	enamelware
bowl
for
2 hours.
Drain well, do not rinse; return to bowl.
Add sugar, vinegar and dill weed.	Let stand, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cover bowl while cucumbers are standing.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: toffee brittle
directions: Cook sugar, butter and nuts to 300° with candy thermometer. Spread on buttered foil, spreading thin.
Scatter milk chocolate chips on top, spreading with knife when melting.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Can place some chopped pecans on top, if desired.

title: easy no-bake cookies
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Let stand 5 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Flavor of pudding determines flavor of cookie.
So good!

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 4 minutes; cool.
Mix together bananas and lemon juice in blender.
Add cooled sugar water and freeze. (May be frozen for a month.)
Thaw in refrigerator overnight and add orange juice, pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: raisin cupcakes
directions: Soak raisins overnight; save juice.
Drain raisins good; save juice.
Mix ingredients.
Add raisins last.
Fill cups 3/4 full. Bake 18 to 22 minutes at 350°.
Makes 36 to 38 cupcakes.

title: cajun spiced shrimp with rotelle pasta
directions: In a
small
bowl,
mix
spices.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet and add garlic and spices.
Turn off heat. Add
shrimp.
Toss	to
coat
in
spices.
Cook
pasta according to	directions.
Toss
with
2 tablespoons of butter and set aside.
Saute shrimp in spice mixture until pink (3 to 4 minutes). Add
to
pasta.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of butter to remaining spice mix left from shrimp.
Add onion, zucchini, tomato and parsley.
Saute
for
3 to 4 minutes.
Add to pasta mixture. Serve
immediately.
Makes	4 to 5 main course servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into bite size pieces.
Place in large pan.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Add chopped celery and onion.
Cook hamburger and drain off fat.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup of water (more or less).
Cover and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Grease tube pan with vegetable spray and flour.
In mixing bowl, combine applesauce, vanilla and almond extract.
Set aside. In second bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Set aside.
In third bowl, beat egg whites until foamy, adding sugar slowly until peaks form.
Drizzle milk mixture and flour mixture into egg foam. Pour batter in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.
Calories:
Fat:
trace.
Cholesterol:
0 gm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water. When it begins to cool and thicken, add orange juice, pineapple and celery.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and pie filling.
Pour mixture in lightly greased dish (9 x 9-inch) and refrigerate until set.
Blend sour cream and softened cream cheese together.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
After salad has congealed, spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Wash and cut up tomatoes.
Chop onions and celery.
Cook tomatoes and next 4 ingredients until celery is tender.
Put through a sieve.
Rub flour and butter into a smooth paste, thinned with tomato juice.
Add to boiling soup.
Add salt, sugar and pepper.
(For smoother consistency, put through sieve again.) Seal by processing 15 minutes in water bath.

title: sweedesh cream wafers
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, cream and flour.
Cover and chill. Roll out 1/3 of dough at a time.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds. Prick center with fork.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes until light brown.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: To make crust, sift first 3 ingredients together.
Combine oil and milk; blend well.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Remove 2/3 cup mixture and set aside.
Press remainder on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Toss together peaches, 1 cup sugar and cinnamon; turn into crust.
To reserved 2/3 cup flour mixture, add brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix well.
Crumble this topping over peach filling.
Bake at 425°
for 15 to 20 minutes; reduce heat to 350°
and bake until filling is bubbly in center and topping is golden.

title: squash pecan casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix all ingredients except nuts and cracker crumbs. Pour into large buttered casserole dish. Top with nuts and cracker crumbs. Bake 20 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage in skillet.
Pour 1 tablespoon sausage oil into potatoes for frying. Add peppers and onion.
Cover until potatoes are done. Add the eggs. Mix constantly until eggs are cooked in. Tastes great with toast.
Serves 4 people.

title: mocha cake
directions: Cream crisco and sugar.
Add 1 egg yolk at a time, then add coffee and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda 3 times. Add alternately with buttermilk and sour cream to cream mix.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in egg whites.
Makes 4 (8-inch) layers or 3 (9-inch) layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: manicotti crepes
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together until smooth.
Fill center of crepe with 3 tablespoons mixture and roll up.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: buckeyes
directions: In a bowl, mix oleo, peanut butter and powdered sugar well for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll into small balls.

title: creamy zucchini casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in 4 tablespoons melted margarine. Stir in 1/2 box stuffing mix and all the seasoning packet.
Mix soup and sour cream together and stir into mixture.
Put into greased casserole.
Melt the other 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix with the rest of the stuffing mix and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and bake in a
9 x 13-inch pan at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to a moderate oven (350°) and bake 30 minutes longer. Serve hot or cold.

title: crunchy peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and beaten eggs.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Drop by rounded balls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until brown, at 350°.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: *Sour Milk:
To sour milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar to milk.

title: easy color cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, vanilla, water and egg.
Mix in brown sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add M&M's.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter and margarine. Add brown sugar, sugar, egg, flour and baking soda. Drop cookie dough from spoon. Press down with a fork to make a pattern on the cookie. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: southern kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, celery, bell pepper, onion and pimento.
Mix well. Set aside.
Combine sugar, oil and vinegar, heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Mix this mixture with the veggie mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water until completely dissolved.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish and chill until set.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over set jello.
Refrigerate.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine in a large skillet. Add rice and cook until rice turns golden. Add other ingredients quickly.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: braised steak
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until light brown.
Drain; crumble and reserve.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Add steak; brown well on both sides.
Add wine, water, salt, parsley, pepper, bouillon cubes and reserved crumbled bacon.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Cover.
Simmer over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until steak is almost fork-tender.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Put all ingredients into large bowl at once.
Stir until well mixed and do not use mixer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart pan, combine butter and cocoa.
Stir over medium heat until butter is melted and mixture is well blended. Remove from heat; stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and egg whites; beat until well blended.
Stir in butter; blend well. Spread batter evenly in an oiled 9-inch square baking pan. Sprinkle walnuts over batter.
Bake at 325° until brownies feel dry on top (about 35 minutes).
Let cool in pan on a rack, then cut into 2 1/4-inch squares.
Store airtight.
Makes about 16 brownies.

title: crunch-top potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan at 375°.
Add single layer of potatoes and turn once in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake 1/2 hour or until done.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Spread crescent roll dough on 13-inch pizza pan and pinch seams together.
Bake until lightly browned. Remove from oven and let cool completely.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss first 7 ingredients together and chill for 2 to 3 hours. Just before serving, mix in shoestring potatoes.
This is good served with fresh fruit and melon and a croissant.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream, mushrooms (and juice from mushrooms).
Add chicken.
Melt butter in large skillet and add stuffing.
Mix until browned.
Put 1/2 of the crumbs on the bottom of a shalloow baking dish.
Pour chicken mixture over and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until it bubbles.
(May also be mixed the day before using).

title: gloria's orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice in blender.
Cover and blend until smooth; about 10 seconds.
Add ice cubes one at a time and blend until most of ice is crushed; about one minute.
Makes about 16 ounces of a foamy drink.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, parsley, garlic powder and salt.
Add soups and pepper.
Blend in sour cream and milk.
Place in casserole.

title: walnut cocoa fudge
directions: Have ready walnuts and graham crackers.
In skillet, mix the first six ingredients.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes or soft boil stage.
Remove from fire; cool until you can hold hand on bottom of skillet.
Beat a little; add nuts and crackers and beat until well blended.
Pour into buttered pan and cut into squares when cool.

title: club day chicken
directions: Mix stuffing with broth and margarine.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken, onions, celery, mayonnaise, chestnuts and salt.
Spread over first mixture. Spread with remaining stuffing.
Beat eggs slightly and add milk. Pour over stuffing.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. Take out 1 hour before baking and spread with soup.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 10 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook
meat
until brown; drain
grease;
add
remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat approximately 30 minutes or so. Serve on fresh hamburger buns.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Pound each chicken breast to 1/4 inch. thickness.
Cut cheese and ham slices in half.
Layer on chicken; roll to enclose cheese and ham.
Secure with toothpicks. Mix paprika, breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, oregano and basil in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken rolls in margarine; roll in crumb mixture to coat.
Place rolls seam side down in a baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Stir slightly.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle water on top.
Add coconut and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: 20 minute chicken parmesan
directions: Using palm of hand flatten chicken to even thickness.
Dip chicken into egg, then coat with crumbs.
Brown chicken in skillet with melted margarine.
Brown on both sides.
Add spaghetti sauce. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley, cover.
Simmer 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cranberry pudding
directions: Combine flour, molasses, cranberries and nuts in a bowl.
Add soda to the hot water and pour into bowl; mix lightly.
Pour into greased 1-quart mold.
Cover tightly with foil.
Steam over boiling water for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve warm with Vanilla sauce. Serves 6.
Double recipe for larger mold and add another hour steaming.
(Can also be baked in flat pan.)

title: cheese salad spread
directions: In a 1-quart bowl, combine all ingredients; stir gently to mix.
Cover; chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours so flavors blend.
Spread on bread or crackers or use to stuff quartered tomatoes.
Yields 2 1/2 cups salad spread.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn to measure 6 quarts.
Boil all other ingredients except soda for 5 minutes.
Add soda and whip.
Pour over corn. Mix well.
Bake in dishpan for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy lunch
directions: Simmer in 2 tablespoons olive oil ground beef until tender, peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Remove from heat.
Mix together in pan:
flour, cornstarch, oil and water.
Stir over medium heat. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer to thickness desired. (This sauce can be omitted and McCormick white sauce mix can be used.)
Mix with meat mixture and serve over toast, mashed or baked potato.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray waffle iron with Pam.
Preheat iron on waffle setting.
Pour 1 cup batter evenly onto preheated iron.
Close unit and bake until light goes off (about 5 minutes). Makes 2 (4 section) waffles.

title: pasta salad italiano
directions: Pour dressing over broccoli, olives and tomatoes.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator at least 3 hours.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Combine vegetable mixture, noodles, cheese and bacon. Toss with marinade.

title: creamy chicken, apples, and sweet potatoes
directions: Combine 1/2 tsp. salt, 1/4 tsp pepper, 1/2 tsp thyme and sprinkle over both side of chicken.
In skillet melt 1 tbsp butter over medium-high heat.
Add apples, 1/4 tsp salt to skillet.
Cook turning occasionally until browned, 4-5 minutes.
Remove apples from skillet, reserve.
In same skillet melt 1 tbsp butter and chicken, cook until browned, 4-5 minutes each side and remove.
In same skillet melt remaining butter, and potatoes, onion, and remaining salt, pepper, and thyme.
Cook stirring occasionally until slightly browned 3-4 minutes.
Add juice, cook until reduced by half, 2-3 minutes.
Stir in broth.
Cover and reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer 10 minutes, stir in cream.
Add reserved apples, chicken.
Cook until potatoes are tender and chicken is done.
With slotted spoon transfer chicken, potatoes and apples to serving platter.
Increase heat to high and cook sauce in skillet until thickened.
Stir in parsley.
Spoon over chicken, potatoes, apples.

title: party pink pineapple punch
directions: Combine the pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar and cranberry juice.
Stir.
Add ginger ale at last minute.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: molasses rolled cookies
directions: Mix molasses, sugar and shortening together.
Dissolve baking soda in water.
Mix together with molasses mixture.
Add ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour and let set 1 hour.
Roll out; cut out.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Use cookie cutter for different holidays such as Christmas trees for Christmas, etc.

title: strawberry rhubarb or fruit cobbler
directions: *Can substitute choice of fruit.
Blueberries with peaches is good.

title: sauerbraten meatballs
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, onion, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 2 tablespoons water, salt and pepper. Shape into 1-inch balls. Brown meat balls in small amount of hot fat. Remove meat balls; add 2 1/4 cups water to drippings and bring to boil. Stir in bouillon cubes, sugar, raisins, 1/4 cup bottled lemon juice and ginger snap crumbs. Add meat balls; cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes. Turn meat balls, spooning sauce over. Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: texas cornbread salad
directions: Chop onion, tomato, green pepper and pickles; mix together. Cook cornbread and bacon according to package directions.
Crumble cornbread (set aside).
Crumble bacon (set aside).
Mix pickle juice and salad dressing together (set aside).

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple in bottom of large cake pan.
Spread evenly. Pour in pie filling and spread evenly.
Pour in cake mix and spread evenly.
Cut butter into pats and place on top of cake mix; cover evenly.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: quick chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Combine spaghetti, onion and pepper mixture, soup, pimentos, chicken and 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda.
Mix orange slices, raisins, walnuts and coconut and then add to the flour mixture.
Combine butter, eggs, sugar and buttermilk and combine all material.
Pour into greased and floured 4 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: hershey's chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix baking powder and salt with flour.
Alternate mixing with 1 pound can of Hershey's syrup, which takes the place of milk.
Bake in a greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: steak and rice dish
directions: Fry steaks until almost done in Wesson oil.
Drain.
In long pan, place steaks on one end.
Pour box of rice on other end.
Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Sprinkle gravy mix on top.
Cook at 400° until rice is done.
Serve as a one dish meal.

title: crunchy potato bake
directions: Mix milk and water in a bowl until smooth.
Add potatoes, onion, egg, salt and cayenne pepper and beat until light and fluffy.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix the corn flakes, cheese and margarine and spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: california walking salad
directions: In a bowl, mix grapes, apple, raisins and peanuts.
Carefully remove lettuce leaves from head, one at a time.
Put 1/2 cup of fruit-nut mixture in each lettuce cup.
Serve out of hand.
Makes 6 to 8 salads.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth according to package directions. Add soups to rice; mix well.
Add other ingredients and pour in large casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes, until heated thoroughly and bubbly.

title: confetti bites(appetizer)
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil leaves and garlic powder.
Spread thinly over cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables such as broccoli, red and green sweet peppers, tomatoes and slivers of carrot.
Top with freshly grated Jack cheese and cut in 2-inch squares before serving.

title: fried apples
