directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Peel and slice apples.
Put in pan with bacon grease.
Cook, covered, until nearly tender.
Add water and finish cooking.
Crumble bacon over apples before serving.

title: mushroom medley
directions: Brown and cook meat until done.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook about 1/2 hour.
Add 1 small bag of noodles.
Do not stir after putting in noodles.
Add 1 cup of water and cook over low heat until noodles are done.
Add about 4 slices of American cheese.

title: rye bread
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, molasses and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large bowl and sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Add caraway seed and rye flour; beat well.
Add enough white flour to make dough. Knead about 7 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double.

title: sinfully delicious pecans
directions: Beat egg whites in mixer bowl until very stiff peaks form. Add vanilla and brown sugar; mix well.
Fold in pecan halves. Remove each pecan half to greased baking sheet with fork.
Bake at 200° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 12 (1/4 cup) servings.

title: scalloped potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole and arrange 2 cups potato slices in casserole dish.
Put 1/2 of the onions on top of potatoes.
Put remaining potatoes and onions on top of this.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown beef.
Sprinkle soup mix over meat.
Stir in water.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt. Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Filling should be slightly unset in the center than around edge.

title: mother's rice pudding
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs with the butter and 3 tablespoons of the sugar, working it together with your fingers until it is all well blended.
Press the mixture evenly onto the bottom of
a 10-inch spring-form cake pan, using a potato masher to make a flat crust.

title: sweet and sour pasta
directions: Cook pasta to tender and drain.
Empty in large mixing bowl and add the vegetable oil; stir.
Let set for 5 minutes; drain off excess oil.
Add all remaining ingredients.

title: jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and water.
Cool.
Add sour cream, oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Set overnight.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
In a pot, put the remaining ingredients.
Boil a few minutes until sugar is dissolved. Pour over cabbage.
Blend and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice with mixer.
Add pineapple and nuts; fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in pot.
Add onion and ground beef and salt.
Stir and brown meat.
Add celery and carrots.
Stir 5 minutes.
Add broth, tomato juice, water and meat loaf.
Mix spaghetti and bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat and cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place pie filling in greased, 1-quart dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: spiced cranberry orange mold
directions: Stir boiling water into jello in a large bowl.
Stir 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in diced oranges.
Pour into 5 cup jello mold.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.
Excellent with turkey at Thanksgiving time.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp in a single layer in a baking dish.
Melt the butter in a small saucepan, add oil and all the spices and mix well.
Drizzle over the shrimp.
Bake for 8 minutes at 450°. Remove from oven.
Preheat broiler, then place shrimp under the broiler to brown, about 5 minutes total.

title: hot apple slices
directions: Slice apple as if you are making a pie. Place slices in a saucepan and pour in sugar-free soda. Heat until it boils. Serve hot with low-fat ice cream on top or frozen yogurt.

title: key lime cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix all ingredients together well; pour into pan.
Bake at 350°.
Baking time depends on what type of pan you are using.
Bake cupcakes for 15 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes.
Check for doneness with a toothpick.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and Karo.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Stir in peanuts gradually so you don't lose the boil.
Stirring constantly, keep at a rolling boil until peanuts pop and turn brown.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and soda, stirring well. Place on well-greased cookie sheet, allowing room for brittle to spread.
When completely cool, break into pieces.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems finely to make 1/3 cup.
Cook and stir chopped mushrooms, onions and green pepper in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bread crumbs, salt, thyme, turmeric and pepper.
Heat butter in shallow baking dish until melted.
Fill precooked mushrooms with stuffing.
Place mushrooms in dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Set on broil and broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 2 minutes.
If desired, add some browned ground sausage in mixture and sprinkle with shredded
Monterey Jack cheese.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add eggs, oil, pecans, vanilla and apples.
Stir well with spoon.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: beef-cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, pepper and onion; drain.
In casserole dish, layer cabbage and beef mixture.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mongolian beef
directions: Cut beef across grained strips, then into 1 1/2-inch squares. Combine 2 tablespoons cornstarch, 1 tablespoon teriyaki sauce, sherry and garlic in a medium bowl; stir in beef.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add nuts; set aside.
Mix well and cool slightly margarine and brown sugar and blend in egg, well beaten.
Add flour mixture little at a time.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and cover with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and red wine vinegar. Chill for 1 hour.
Add to remaining ingredients and toss.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add Cool Whip and strawberries.
Stir until melted.
Tear cake in pieces and put in a 9-inch square dish.
Pour mixture over cake and chill (covered) overnight.

title: corn crisped chicken
directions: Dip chicken in evaporated milk.
Roll in mixture of corn flake crumbs, salt and pepper.
Place in shallow baking pan lined with aluminum foil (that's right, no shortening!).
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until drumstick is tender when pierced with a fork.

title: baked beans
directions: Add brown sugar, catsup, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix everything together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° with lid on.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1 1/2 cups beet liquid.
Place beets in a saucepan along with the reserved liquid.
Combine the cornstarch and sugar.
Add that along with all the other ingredients; mix well.
Cook for 3 minutes over medium heat or until mixture thickens.
Let cool and store in refrigerator.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease muffin tins.
Sift flour into bowl along with salt.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with grapes, strawberries, slices of bananas, apples and oranges.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix soft margarine, mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce. Cut rolls in half - spread mixture on top half. Layer ham, cheese on both packages of rolls. Replace tops. Bake 400 for 10 min.

title: batter for vegetables
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Add to flour.
Add oil.
Beat good with a wire whisk until smooth.
Dip vegetable in batter and deep fry.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, margarine and oil until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add to the first mixture and mix well.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press cookies down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Wrap each shrimp in a half slice of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Cream sugar, Crisco and melted margarine.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Add milk, flour and vanilla alternately.
Beat 10 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Put in cold oven and turn heat to 350°. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Brown onion and bacon in a skillet.
Drain.
Add catsup, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Put beans in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over beans.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together; refrigerate.
Add coconut to taste.

title: jared's grammy lee's hot fudge
directions: Over medium high heat, stir cocoa into butter until smooth. Add sugar and milk.
Blend and bring to full boil, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Ready to serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening.
Beat eggs with 2 cups sugar. Add dry ingredients and melted chocolate and shortening.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars. Add eggs. Add peanut butter. Alternate flour and milk, mixing after each addition. Add soda and vanilla. Mix well and bake in greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool about 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in olive oil and cook until onions are clear.
Add garlic, parsley, tomato sauce and wine, then add rice.
Add smoked sausage or andouille and enough water to cover about 1 inch above ingredients.
Add salt and hot sauce, then stir.
Cook on medium heat until most of the juice is gone, then cover and simmer 1 hour.
This makes a red jambalaya.

title: english muffin meal
directions: Layer in order with cheese on top.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: wilted deli cole slaw(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cabbage is best if shredded in long, very thin shreds.
In a large 3-quart bowl, layer cabbage, green pepper and onion.
In saucepan combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat just to boiling, stirring.
Pour over slaw.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let stand a couple hours (or overnight).
Then refrigerate.
Just before serving, toss salad thoroughly.

title: italian bean soup(low-fat - heart healthy)
directions: In a large kettle, combine rinsed beans and 5 cups cold water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans.
In same pan, combine beans, 5 cups fresh water, undrained tomatoes, onion, bouillon, garlic, Italian seasoning and pepper. Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Mash beans slightly with wooden spoon. Add frozen green beans and simmer until beans are tender.
A hearty, low-fat, meatless soup.
I serve with bran muffins or thick wedges of garlic bread.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Grease 3 (1-1/2 quart) round ovenproof bowls.
In large bowl, combine 2 cups rye flour, orange peel, anise seed and yeast.
In medium saucepan, heat water, honey, margarine and salt until lukewarm.
Gradually add liquid to dry ingredients and beat at low speed until moistened.
Add remaining rye flour and 1 cup flour, beat 2 minutes with wooden spoon, stir in 2 1/2 cups flour or enough to make soft dough.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and cook at 350° for at least 1 1/2 hours; pour off excess grease.

title: chicken noodle and cheese bake
directions: Cook chicken until done (steam).
Cook noodles as directions. Drain; pour noodles in a baking dish.
Mix milk and soup together. Place chicken over noodles; pour soup over.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Place cheese on top; bake until cheese melts.

title: easy dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and place on bottom of square casserole pan. Add fruit filling. Cover with yellow cake mix and nuts. Cut small pieces of margarine and place on top of cake mix. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; cool slightly.
Poke holes in top of cake with straw or pencil.
Mix caramel topping and milk together and heat.
Pour over cake while mixture is hot.
Let it cool, then frost with whipped topping.
Top with crushed candy bars.
Chill.

title: basil carrots
directions: In medium skillet melt the butter or margarine; add the onion and saute until wilted.
Add the sliced carrots.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Cook, covered, simmering 15 to 20 minutes, just until carrots are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Use at least 4 of the following vegetables, chopped: broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, green onions, olives, mushrooms and carrots.

title: low-fat cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat a muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix first eight ingredients in a large bowl.
In a two-cup measure, mix milk, applesauce and egg.
Combine liquid and dry ingredients, mixing just to combine.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups three-quarters full.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yield: 10 muffins.

title: bloody clamdigger
directions: Put some ice cubes in a tall glass. Add clam and tomato juices, vodka and lemon juice. Season to taste with celery salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Garnish with a stick of crisp celery and serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and let set until ready for it. Combine shortening, eggs, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add yeast water and mix.
Add flour and mix well.
Brush a little shortening over dough and place wax paper over top.
Do not seal tight. Refrigerate overnight or until ready to roll out.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thick.
Brush melted butter over top and let rise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes (depends on oven).

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop head of cabbage in food processor. Mix together other ingredients.
Mix all together and chill.

title: sugar & honey nuts
directions: Cook over medium heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Let boil to 242° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until thick, then spread on paper towels on counter to cool.

title: easy strawberry-banana punch
directions: Puree bananas in blender.
Add dry Jell-O and juice to blender; puree to mix together.
Pour into 1 gallon container and add rest of juice plus enough water to make 1 gallon.
Put into freezer until slushy.

title: hamburger pickles
directions: Mix pickles and salt.
Let stand 1 hour and drain good.
Mix in onion.
Mix vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Pour over pickles. Will keep in refrigerator for months.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add flour 1 cup at a time, with 4 eggs alternately, adding 3 eggs each additional time. Add salt stir in pineapple with spatula.
Pour in a greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: summer tea
directions: Steep mint and tea in water, then remove tea bags and mint and stir sugar into mixture until dissolved. Add diluted juices and tea mixture. Add artificial sweetener if desired and water until diluted to taste.

title: applesauce bars
directions: In large bowl, cream applesauce, eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour in 15 x 11 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan finale
directions: Combine crumbs, margarine and sugar; press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread ice cream over crust; freeze at least 1 hour.
Combine pumpkin, sugar and seasoning.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour over ice cream layer; freeze.
Place in refrigerator 5 minutes before serving.

title: salted pecans
directions: Mix all
together and place on a cookie sheet.	Bake in oven at	250°
for 1 hour and stir every 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Mix and bake as directed.
Let cool.
Mix pudding, cream cheese and cold milk together until all are well blended.
After cake is cold, spread pudding mixture on.
Let cake stand for 1 hour, then put on crushed pineapple.
Next, frost with 1 large Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: crispy fried carrots
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; set aside. Beat egg white until foamy.
Stir in buttermilk and hot sauce.
Dip carrots in buttermilk mixture; drain off excess mixture and dredge in cornmeal mix.
Fry carrots in 1-inch hot oil about 2 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve immediately.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: In crock pot, mix butter, eggs, and milk with 2 cups grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni, stir well.
Add last cup of cheese on top.
Do not stir.
Place lid on crock pot.
Cook on high for 3 hours.
Do not stir or open lid while cooking.
Serves eight.

title: hot frito dip
directions: Chop onions and garlic into semi-fine pieces.
Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add 3 cans chopped green chiles.
Drain whole tomatoes through a colander until almost dry.
Add to onions and garlic.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Cut up Velveeta cheese and stir in until melted.
Remove from heat.
Divide into several servings.
Freeze excess.
Can be defrosted and reheated in microwave.
Serve with white tortilla chips for dipping.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix and bake cake following instructions on box.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Beat until stiff.
Fill center of cake with cream cheese mixture.
Then arrange cherries on top of filling and refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: fat-free guacamole
directions: Mash or coarsely process asparagus until almost pureed, but still contains some small chunks.
Add rest of ingredients; cover and refrigerate for several hours, if possible, before use. Yield:
Approximately 2 cups.

Each 2 tablespoons = 6 calories, 0 g total fat, 0 g saturated fat, 0 g polyunsaturated fat, 0 g monounsaturated fat, 0 mg cholesterol, 1.1 g carbohydrate, 0.6 g protein, 50 mg sodium and 0% calories from fat.

title: cherokee harvest salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a bowl.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soup, broth and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.

title: broccoli and beef stir-fry
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and 1/2 cup of water; set aside.
Mix cornstarch with remaining 1/4 cup water; set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok or shallow skillet until hot.
Add broccoli stalks, sliced.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broccoli flowerets; cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Remove broccoli to platter.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil to wok; heat until hot.
Add meat and stir-fry until done.
Add soy sauce.
Add cornstarch mixture; stir until slightly thickened.
Add broccoli and mix well.
Serve over rice.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: quick cheesecakes
directions: Put one wafer in each muffin tin lined with paper cup. Combine all other ingredients. Fill each cup
half full.
Bake at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Spoon on topping when ready to serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until almost tender, drain.
Spray casserole dish with vegetable oil spray.
In a saucepan melt and mix margarine, flour and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
To this mixture add Velveeta cheese, cut into small pieces.
Stir until melted.
Place cabbage in dish, then pour liquid over cabbage.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated.

title: coconut thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Cream butter with sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Combine flour with salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well and form into bars about 1-inch in diameter.
Beat egg white until slightly frothy.
Dip dough balls into egg white, then roll in coconut. Place on greased baking sheets.
Make a "thumbprint" in the center of each cookie and spoon 1/2 teaspoon of preserves into each. Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes or until coconut begins to brown. Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken mediterranean
directions: Place chicken in a large bowl and set aside.
Mix water, lemon juice, grated lemon rind, oregano, garlic salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour the lemon mixture over the chicken and refrigerate covered for 3 to 4 hours, stirring frequently.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Make cake by directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream of coconut and condensed milk together.
Punch holes in cake and pour over the cake while cake is hot.
When cake cools, top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together until smooth.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Let set several hours or overnight.

title: e-z jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Chill milk until flaky.
Whip Jell-O and combine milk and Jell-O.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch pan with graham cracker crust.

title: party size hot dogs
directions: Heat all together and serve.

title: ragalach
directions: Day ahead, mix margarine, cheese and salt until creamy.
Mix in flour. Shape into 14 balls.
Chill overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
On lightly floured cloth covered board, roll each ball to 6-inch circle.
Cut each into quarters.
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto each quarter.
Pinch together edges of dough. Form into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in microwave-safe bowl.
Add noodles.
Stir together.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.
(May need to refrigerate for a few minutes.)

title: cherry o'cream pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Whip the whipping cream until firm and stands in peaks.
Fold this into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Add cherry pie filling on top and refrigerate.
Let set until chilled.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Mix sweet potatoes and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Cook in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Set pan in hot water and cook at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans (medium) or 6 small loaf pans.
Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until lemon colored.
Shred zucchini, salt lightly and squeeze juice out.
Add to mixture.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add to wet mixture and mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pans.
Bake medium loaf pans 50 to 60 minutes and bake small loaf pans 35 minutes.

title: peach pie filling(peelings)
directions: Peelings may be stored in freezer until you have enough to make the filling.
Chill and make pies or dig from frozen stage. The vinegar will not allow the mix to harden.

title: kraut salad
directions: Squeeze kraut dry; add celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar together and pour over vegetable mixture. Let stand for several hours.
Keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: tabouli(parsley and cracked wheat salad)
directions: Cut off stems of parsley, leaving the florets.
Pick leaves off mint stems (if using fresh).
Wash parsley in bowl, rinsing and draining until all sand has disappeared.
Drain well.
Wash mint. Mince the parsley very fine, using a knife or food processor.
Cut the mint in small pieces.

title: southern style coating mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.

title: mock candied sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub squash.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
In a baking dish, mix water, extract and sweetener.
Lay squash, cut side down, in liquid and bake until tender.
Length of time and amount of water, extract and sweetener depend on size of vegetable.
You will find that the liquid will be absorbed into the squash as it bakes.
Remove from oven when fork punctures through as testing potatoes.
Set aside until cool enough to handle.
With tablespoon, scoop pulp from skin.
Discard skin. With fork or electric mixer, mash well.
Place 4 ounces in serving dish.
Dot with butter and serve.

title: shrimp - crab - cheese canapes
directions: Cut 30 (2-inch) white bread rounds and butter one side. Toast bread rounds under the broiler on buttered side only.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredient together.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Cook at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese surprise
directions: Mix
sugar and flour; mix in drained pineapple.
Grease an 8 x 11 1/2-inch pan with butter.
Put pineapple mixture in casserole and
top
with
cheese
and
Ritz cracker crumbs and margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Mix coffee cake ingredients together.
Pour into 2 loaf pans (lightly greased).
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Muffin tins can be used also. Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups of water for a few minutes.
Drain water off and roll raisins in flour, then add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Blend in soda, flavoring and remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at
350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cucumber sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix mayonnaise in sour cream.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Butter mold and pour in mixture.
Store in refrigerator.
(For smoother texture, blend dissolved jello, sour cream and mayonnaise in blender before adding remaining ingredients.
Also, if cucumber seeds are large, remove before chopping.)

title: cucumber soup
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Cook in oleo 10 minutes over low fire, stirring often.
Stir in flour and then gradually add chicken stock, stirring constantly.
Add milk and onion.
Simmer slowly 10 minutes, stirring often.
Cool slightly and put through blender or food processor with half and half and salt and pepper (do in batches if necessary).
Chill thoroughly and serve cold with chopped chives for garnish.

title: quick and easy lemon pie
directions: Put Eagle Brand milk and egg yolks in bowl and mix well.
Then add lemon juice and stir.
Put into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Place meringue on pie, and bake in oven at 350° until it gets brown.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in small amount of oil until tender, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Mix cooked squash with egg, milk, cracker crumbs and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken roger rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Put rice and other ingredients in baking dish; lay chicken on top.
Pour liquid over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Watch that it does not get dry.
Add more juice.

title: beef-stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove seeds.
Cook peppers 5 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Cook ground beef and onion in large skillet until brown; drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce and next 3 ingredients.
Stuff peppers with meat sauce mixture; place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water.
Cook until tender.
Stir in blended sugar and flour.
Cook over low heat.
Stir in nuts, lemon peel and juice.
Pour into pastry shell and use top pastry.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry ice cream(gelato di fragola)
directions: This is an Italian recipe for ice cream.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix raisin bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in very large bowl.
Add beaten eggs, shortening and buttermilk and mix well. Store in refrigerator and us as desired.
For muffins, fill greased tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° in preheated oven, 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks, if covered.
If batter has been in refrigerator, bake a little longer.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar and flour.
Combine egg and 3 tablespoons cold water; add to sugar-flour mixture.
Heat juices; slowly stir small amount into egg mixture; return to hot mixture.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Chill.
Whip cream with 2 tablespoons sugar. Fold into juice mixture.
Makes 3 cups.

title: perez potato soup
directions: Boil the vegetables until tender. Puree, then add milk, cream and salt and pepper.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shell and bake in 300° oven until set (about 1 hour).

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in the refrigerator until ready to use.

title: steak japanese style
directions: Cook the meat to your taste in frying pan; 20 seconds before you finish cooking, make fire maximum strength.
Pour the soy sauce (20cc, an ounce per piece) around the meat; don't put on the meat.
By burning the soy sauce, it makes them taste better and smell better.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla thoroughly.
Add flour and salt.
Stir in.
Roll dough into balls (1 teaspoon per ball).
Beat egg white slightly with fork.
Dip balls in egg white.
Roll in nuts.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press thumb gently in center of each ball.
Place candied cherry in hole.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cover rhubarb with sugar and let stand overnight.
Cook until it begins
to
boil.
Boil	for
5 minutes!
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: frosty drink
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender. Blend on medium until smooth and creamy. Stir if necessary.

title: monterey crepes
directions: Wash and hull strawberries; slice into a bowl.
Peel, halve, pit and slice peaches.
Combine peaches and strawberries; sprinkle with lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Let stand.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix marinade ingredients; stir well. Cover punctured steak. Refrigerate for 2 days (yes), turning often. Grill 20 to 30 minutes. Very tender and delicious.

title: ginger bread
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given, dissolving the soda in the hot water.
Add the well-beaten eggs last.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: picnic potato salad with yogurt dressing
directions: Dice potatoes and mix with other ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: hamburger crunch casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add both cans of soup and 1 can water. Add rice and soy sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°. Sprinkle with chow mein noodles and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute butter and onion in saucepan.
Add Ro-Tel, drained saving liquid.
Add 2 1/4 cups Ro-Tel juice and water; bring to boil.
Add rice; bring to boil.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Pour rice mixture into casserole and stir in Velveeta.
Stir in thawed shrimp and mix part of the shredded cheese in mixture, saving enough to cover top.
Sprinkle black olives on top and heat through 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
May add chopped green onions on top for color.
Serve with salsa for individual tastes.

title: fried rice(good party dish)
directions: Wash rice well.
Using skillet with cover, add 1/4 cup oil. Add raw rice; cover and brown, shaking and stirring so as not to burn.
Add 1/2 cup each of broth and bean sprout liquor.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Repeat until all liquid is absorbed and rice is cooked (about 1 1/4 hours cooking time).
Add onion; cover 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 5 more minutes, covered.
Mix carefully.
Sprinkle eggs and parsley for garnish.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Add corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare and cut potatoes in quarters or eighths.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Moisten potatoes and shake, a few at a time, in bag, coating well.
Melt butter in 9X13 inch pan. Place potatoes in single layer in pan.
Bake for 1 hour, turning once during baking.
When brown, sprinkle with parsley.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb, pineapple and sugar for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 2 (3 ounce) packages jello.
Mix well and pour into pint or jelly jars.
Seal with paraffin wax.

title: honey chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut each wing in half at the joint. Place in a single layer in a shallow 3-quart baking dish.

title: lillian hellman's pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a good pot in order given.
Cover and bake about 3 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In large microwave-safe bowl, place the creme drops, peanut butter and butter.
Cover and microwave only long enough to melt the candy (do not overcook).
Stir until well blended and spread in buttered dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Put ribs in baking pan and brown in a 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Drain fat.
Combine all ingredients for sauce.
Cook over medium heat until smooth and glossy and is thick.
Spoon 1/2 of the sauce over the ribs.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue cooking for 25 minutes.
Turn ribs over and cover with remaining sauce; cook for another 25 to 30 minutes.

title: very berry salad
directions: Mix together.
Serve.
You can add grapes, pineapple, kiwi, banana, apple, nectarine, peach, just about any fruit you may have and it will be delicious.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all of the ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook onion and margarine until tender. Drain corn; save juice. Add corn juice and potatoes to onion mixture. Cook until tender. Add corn, salt and pepper; stir 1/4 cup milk with the flour. Stir until smooth. Add rest of milk to corn; stir in flour mixture. Stir while it is cooking to keep from sticking. Let it cook until it thickens, about 5 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix tapioca pudding, orange Jell-O and water together in pan; place on heat, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Boil for 1 minute; semi cool and fold in Dream Whip which has been whipped with milk.
Add mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple.
Put in loaf pan and refrigerate.

title: jim's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and 1 tablespoon water.
Beat sugar, oil and 1/2 cup warm water.
Dissolve the ingredients together; stir in flour.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down, then roll out and cut into squares.
Pat center with butter or oil, then fold over.
Let rise again.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix milk and cracker crumbs.
Add fruit, then last add nuts. Have pound cake pan lined with foil and waxed paper.
Pack mixture firmly in pan and let stay in refrigerator at least 24 hours before cutting.

title: flour tortillas(tortillas de harina)
directions: Sift dry ingredients, add shortening, working it into the flour.
Stir in 1 cup of water and form into a ball.
If necessary, use more water until bowl is clear of all dough. Knead well on floured board and make balls size of an egg.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Roll out with rolling pin until they are the size of a salad plate.
Place in hot ungreased skillet or griddle on top of stove and cook about 2 minutes on one side. Turn over to other side and cook 1 minute longer.
These are best when freshly made, although you can warm them over.

title: cornmeal yeast rolls
directions: Combine 1
1/2 cups flour and yeast.
In a pot, heat to 115° to 120° the milk, margarine, brown sugar and salt. Add to flour and
yeast. Stir. Add egg.	Beat for 3 1/2 minutes.
Add the cornmeal. Beat until combined. Add remainder of flour. Mix well. Turn
out
on
floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Grease bowl.
Let rise until double in size. Turn out on
floured surface
again
and
divide
into
rolls.
Put on greased pan. Let raise again. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add oil.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla. Spoon into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Do not underbake or cake will fall.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top before baking.

title: christmas berries
directions: Cover almond slivers with green food coloring and set aside. Blend coconut and pecans.
Mix with Eagle brand milk and 2 boxes of Jello.
Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Form into strawberry shapes. Roll in remaining box of strawberry Jello and make stem from green almond sliver.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Stir flour, sugar, soda and salt together in a large mixing bowl.
Add cereal and mix well. Stir in eggs, oil and buttermilk. Mix thoroughly and store in refrigerator in covered container. Mixture will keep 3 to 4 weeks. As needed, fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake 20 minutes or until done. Makes 50 to 60 medium muffins.

title: macaroni au gratin
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Put a layer at the bottom of a baking dish.
Make the sauce by blending in saucepan, 3 level tablespoons of butter (or margarine) with the same quantity of flour.
Add slowly 1 1/2 cups milk and stir until the sauce boils.
Cook 3 minutes and season with salt and pepper.
Add 2/3 of the cheese to the sauce and put layer over the macaroni in the dish.
Proceed in this way, first macaroni, then sauce until the dish is full, having sauce for the last layer.
Sprinkle the remainder of the cheese over the top. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in reserved beet liquid, the vinegar and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in beets.
Cook until heated through. Makes 2 servings.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Crush or grind vanilla wafers.
Add raisins and walnuts and mix well.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the mixture.
Mix well and press well into rolls.
Wrap tightly in foil or waxed paper. Place in refrigerator until ready to slice and serve.

title: super-easy squash quiche
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, onion, squash and cheese; mix well.
Add biscuit mix and blend well.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Chop it up.
Mix all together (except crackers and margarine); put in a baking dish.
Top with 1 package crumbled Ritz crackers.

title: cheesy broccoli and rice
directions: Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until melted.

title: deviled eggs deluxe
directions: Boil eggs, then cut eggs in half.
Remove egg yolks, and mash egg yolks in a bowl.
Add mustard, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and mayonnaise; mix well.
Stir in tuna and curry.
Stuff in halved egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: super cocoa
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together in medium size saucepan (use a wooden spoon).
Mix together water and Carnation evaporated milk. Add the Carnation milk and water mixture to cocoa in saucepan and stir until smooth.
Heat over low heat 5 to 6 minutes.
Put a marshmallow in each cup and pour cocoa over marshmallow.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Boil rotini in lightly salted water; drain and cool.
Add oil to noodles and mix.
Pour dressing over all and mix.
Refrigerate. Will keep a long time.
Just stir up occasionally to re-coat with dressing.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and eggs together.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mutt's cheese wafers
directions: Cream together butter and cheese.
Add flour, Rice Krispies and red pepper.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill. Ready to eat in 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Serve on lettuce with crackers.

title: summer fruit bread
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Gradually add flour and baking powder. Fold in fruit and nuts. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes in 4 small loaf pans or 1 hour in 2 large loaf pans or Bundt pan.

title: chicken noodle soup dump
directions: Dump all 13 things.
Cook on high heat for 3 hours.
Cook on simmer/low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: marinated vegetables(better made at least a day ahead.)
directions: Drain peas, corn and green beans, then mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Will keep for several days.

title: amish hot hamburgers
directions: Cover round steak and onion with water and cook 1 hour. Drain.
Add milk, mustard, salt, pepper and crackers.
Simmer slowly about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Serve on hot buns.

title: club cracker bars
directions: Boil lightly together 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, crushed graham crackers, milk and margarine.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with Club crackers.
Pour mixture over Club crackers and add another layer of Club crackers.
Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour over top layer of crackers. Chill or freeze before cutting.

title: health bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl large enough to hold all. Mix wet ingredients all together and add to dry ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick tests done.

title: beef and brown rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain off fat. Combine all ingredients in large casserole, except pineapple chunks.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
During the last 10 minutes, pour over pineapple chunks with juice.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with enough milk to be dipping consistency. Cut chipped beef finely.
Chop green onions.
Blend all ingredients together and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald milk. In a large ovenproof bowl, mix remaining ingredients. When milk is scalded, add Grape-Nuts. Pour milk and Grape-Nuts into egg mixture.
Place bowl into pan of water and place in oven. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Before cooking, you can sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: nachos casserole no. 2
directions: In a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish, spread uncooked rice in bottom.
In skillet, brown meat; drain.
Stir in corn, tomatoes, taco seasoning mix and water; mix well.
Spoon meat mixture over rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with tortilla chips, then cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.
Total Time: 40 minutes.

title: marshmallow pecan candies
directions: Put the sugar and nuts into a heavy-based saucepan over medium heat and stir until the sugar starts to melt.
Continue to cook, stirring frequently with a wooden spoon, until the sugar is a dark caramel color.
Dip the bottom of the pan quickly into cold water to stop the cooking; remove immediately.
Drop small spoonfuls of the nut mixture (about 3 to 4 nuts in each) onto an oiled baking sheet.
Allow to cool, then transfer immediately to an airtight container.
Layer with wax paper and keep tightly sealed.
Yield: 1 to 1 1/2 dozen candies.

title: sour cream mushroom chicken
directions: Mix soup and sprinkles with water in baking dish. Add chicken and bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Add sherry and bake 30 minutes more or until done.
Serve over rice or noodles. (Add water to gravy to thin, if needed.)
Serves 6.

title: mulled sauterne cup
directions: Combine and heat slowly to just below boiling.
Serve in preheated cups.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Put chicken, chicken broth and water in a large pan with lid. Boil until the meat has fallen off bones or starts to shred. Remove bones and add garlic.

title: bourbon sauce
directions: Mix milk, sugar, egg, butter and salt in top of double boiler. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Add bourbon.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Put one piece of steak on wooden skewer until all meat is used.
Pan-fry until done.

title: sausage potato casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain. In a bowl, combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper. In an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 the potatoes, soup mix and sausage.
Repeat layers. Cover. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until potatoes are tender. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven about 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in bowl together. Put in casserole dish. Crush up 2 C of corn flakes and sprinkle over top. Pour another 1/2 stick of melted butter over top. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turkey buffet casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted boiling water until tender; drain. Dice broccoli stems but leave flowerets whole.
Meanwhile, in saucepan over low heat, melt butter; stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.
In greased casserole or 8-inch baking dish, arrange noodles, broccoli stems and turkey.
Pour cheese sauce over all.
Arrange broccoli flowerets on top; sprinkle on almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: creamy praline patties
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar and soda.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Stir in cream.
Bring to boil over medium heat. Stir occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and pecans.
Beat mixture until thick, 2 to 3 minutes.
Drop from metal spoons on wax paper on in nut cups.
Makes 24 to 30 (1 1/2-inch) patties.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish on bottom of greased dish.
Pour soup over fish. Place stuffing on top.
Pat with butter.
Bake uncovered 350° for 1/2 hour.
Top with cheese and put in oven until it melts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put butter, rice and water in baking dish; let soak for few minutes.
Add celery, onion and mushroom soup.
Thaw, drain and break apart broccoli.
Add to baking dish.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add cheese and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: fudge pecan ripple layer cake
directions: Grease 2, 9-inch round cake pans; line with wax paper.
Grease and flour wax paper. Set aside.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in cinnamon.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add catsup, pickle relish, Worcestershire sauce and Season-All seasoned salt.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: hot dip in rye bread
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and garlic salt. Hollow out rye bread (not too deep).
Put mixture in bread.
Wrap in foil.
Put on cookie sheet and put broken bread pieces around it.
Heat at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with the broken pieces and crackers to use with the dip.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream egg and sugar together.
Sift flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon and add to creamed mixture.
Add apples and nuts and blend all together with mixer.
Pour into cake pans and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and shape into bite size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ribble soup
directions: Cook beef well done.
Remove from broth.
Add corn, salt and pepper to boiling broth and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Make ribble by using 2 eggs slightly stirred to which you add flour so that when rubbed between the palms of your hand you have small crumbly ribble.
Add ribble to the boiling broth and corn, stirring as you add.
Cook a few minutes.
The ribble will look like big grains of rice when done.
Take care not to let boil over.

title: chocolate chip treasure cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a small bowl, mix crumbs, flour and baking powder. In a large bowl, beat Eagle Brand and butter until smooth. Add crumb mixture. Mix well. Stir in rest of ingredients. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well. Combine rest of ingredients.
Fold all ingredients with wooden spoon.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans or use 4 small foil loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, 5 minutes or done.
Test with toothpick.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in shape of French fries.
Cover skillet with shortening and melt.
Place potatoes, onions, salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Add water to prevent from sticking.

title: german hamburger
directions: Fry beef, onion, sauerkraut and sauce; cool.
Prepare roll mix as directed, shape into balls and flatten.
Put hamburger mixture in center.
Pull up dough around meat and seal.
Put in muffin cup in muffin pan.
Let rise, bake until brown.

title: spice cake
directions: In bowl, blend together first 5 ingredients on low speed; then beat on high for 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until brown.
Melt margarine and drizzle over hot cake.
Sprinkle cinnamon sugar mixture on top.

title: chicken salad
directions: Place chopped chicken in a large bowl.
Season with lemon juice, salt and red pepper.
Add mayonnaise and a bit of pickle vinegar to moisten.
Can add chopped nuts.
Apples or grapes may be added, if desired.

title: butter rolls
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, butter, sugar and yeast that has been crumbled into 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir well, add flour.
Let rise until light and divide into 2 or 3 parts.
Roll out like pie crust, but not as thin.
Spread melted butter over dough.
Cut into wedge shaped parts.
Roll from wide part to point.
Let rise again and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: strawberry dumplings
directions: Immerse strawberries in cold water to rinse, immediately turn into colander to drain.
Remove stems and cut berries in half.
In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, combine berries with 1/3 cup sugar, water and lemon peel.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Melt all of the ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan greased with butter.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix according to directions on package. Line a pie plate, fluting a high edge.
Combine flour with brown sugar; cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Measure 1 cup and reserve for topping.
Pour remaining crumbs into pie shell.
Add soda to water; stir in molasses.
Pour over crumbs in pie shell.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top. Bake in preheated oven (350°).

title: corn salad
directions: Mix with mayonnaise; cover and refrigerate overnight, if possible.
tags: whole kernel white Shoe Peg corn

title: 10-cup cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter, white sugar and brown sugar. Add remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mollie's fried okra
directions: Select a good mess of small okra pods (they are more tender). Slice into little wheels," but be sure to wash the fuzzies off first.
Prepare the batter in a large bowl.
Whip the ingredients together; once smooth add the flour until it looks fairly thick and will not run in the skillet.
Dump in your okra wheels and mix with a spoon.
It should look ropey.
On a hot, flat buttered skillet, drop your okra patties (about a heaping tablespoonful) until they are about the size of a silver dollar pancake.
They should be flat and fry until they are golden brown.
Place on paper towels while they cool to get rid of some extra grease (and calories).
Enjoy!

title: hot pickled eggs
directions: Warm vinegar with salt.
Put eggs in jar.
Pour vinegar, peppers and garlic in jar and shake.
Seal lid and enjoy.

title: oatmeal tasty muffins
directions: All women are possessed of a common disease, and that is clipping out various recipes.
These collections grow to a formidable number with dishes to serve both winter and summer.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.	Add flour and buttermilk alternating.
Add cocoa, coloring, salt, soda and vanilla.
Mix together and pour into three 9-inch round cake pans. Bake 325 for 30 minutes.
Depending on stove temperature.
Let cool.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Place apples and undiluted apple juice in pan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer covered 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Gently stir cornstarch into apple mixture. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer covered until thickened. Stir in cinnamon.
Fill pastry shell with apple mixture and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May make struedel topping if you wish instead of top crust.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together the day before.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ribs. Pour over ribs in a baking pan. Be sure ribs are covered with liquid. Bake in a 325° oven for about 2 hours or until done.

title: lori's cheese cake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and sugar.
Press in bottom of buttered pan (9 x 13-inches).
Mix Dream Whip as package says; set aside.

title: broiled swordfish(for two people)
directions: Wash fish and pat dry.
Place steaks on a cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spoon over fish and spread evenly.
Sprinkle seasoning over top.
Broil on middle rack until golden brown.
Check for doneness (fish should flake with a fork).
Bake at 350° for a few more minutes, if necessary.
Serve with your favorite vegetable or salad.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a
large
pot,
mix	sugar,	milk, cocoa and butter. Bring to	boil,
stirring constantly.
Let boil 1 1/2 minutes. Do not stir
during
this time.
Remove from fire and quickly stir in peanut
butter
and oatmeal.
On wax paper, spoon out cookies.

title: coffee cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut steak in small pieces.
Brown meat and place in casserole dish.
Add soup and water.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Cover with foil for about 30 minutes.
Remove cover and finish cooking.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Mash clove of garlic with 2 tsp. salt.
Add all ingredients in heavy saucepan and simmer about 2 1/2 hours.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix in all ingredients until well mixed.
For each pancake, pour 1/4 cup mixture on hot well-greased griddle and spread into a 4-inch cake.
Brown on first side; turn and brown on second side. Makes about 2 cups (8 pancakes).

title: banana pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 1/2-inch muffin cups or use paper liners.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water, pecans, oil and mashed banana.
Stir with spoon until well blended.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Keep muffins stored in airtight containers.

title: mom's homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Heat the
quart
of milk and evaporated milk in a large kettle.
Mix
the cornstarch, salt, cocoa and sugar in the one cup of milk.
When the milk in the kettle starts to steam, add the other
milk
mixture and the egg yolk mixture.
Cook until thick like
pudding,
then
add
the
gelatin
which
has been dissolved in
a
little bit of water.
Cool, refrigerate until ready to put into
the ice cream freezer.
When ready to make the ice cream, add to the cooled mixture:
the quart of cream, vanilla and stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Chop apples and mix together with cranberries.
Put in greased glass dish.
Combine other ingredients until crumbly and spread over the top.
Bake at 385° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brussels sprouts with vidalia onion butter
directions: Cook onion in butter on very low heat, until soft and brown. Cook Brussels sprouts in chicken stock until just tender.
Drain. Toss with onion butter.
Add salt and pepper to your taste. Yield: 10 servings.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Stir in mushrooms, crabmeat, crackers and parsley. Spread over fish and roll with seam side down.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a 9x13 baking dish, combine apples, lemon juice, cinnamon, nutmeg, and sugar.
In a small bowl, mix flour or graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar, and butter together using a fork or your fingers.
Work this until small even crumbles form.
Sprinkle this mixture evenly over apples and bake 15-20 minutes in a 400 degree oven.
Serve apple crisp with small scoops of ice cream.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown beef and onions; add seasonings and tomato sauce. In a casserole dish, alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce and cheese. Add water; cover tightly and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Do not freeze.

title: lamb patties
directions: Mix thoroughly the meat, bread crumbs, parsley, dill, egg, garlic and salt.
Shape mixture into 4 patties.
Wrap bacon slice around edge of each patty; secure with wooden picks.
Place patties on rack in broiler pan.
Broil for 15 minutes; turn once.

title: polynesian rice(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add garlic and almonds; cook until almonds are light brown.
Add the soy sauce and the rice.
Be careful not to salt without tasting as the soy sauce is salty.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in sherbet and cool. Add oranges.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate.

title: ham loaf
directions: Make the first 5 ingredients into a loaf. Bring the last 3 ingredients to a boil. Add a couple of pinches of ground cloves and a pinch of salt. Baste loaf 2 or 3 times with this mixture.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; make well.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts.

title: m.a.b.o. muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, oats and cinnamon; set aside.
Measure bran and milk into mixing bowl. Stir to combine and let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add egg, syrup and oil.
Combine, then add shredded apple.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and stir only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brownish.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese.
Layer on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix avocado with lemon juice and garlic.
Blend in onion, salt and pepper; layer next.
Prepare hamburger as directed on taco mix package.
When cool, layer next.
Spread salsa on top of hamburger.
Sprinkle grated Jack cheese on top of salsa (you can heat dip at this point).
Sprinkle shredded lettuce over cheese, then tomatoes and black olives.
Spread thin layer of sour cream on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and combine with buttermilk.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans (optional).
Pour in an unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 275°, then increase to 300° and cook for about 50 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in casserole and then put in mixture. Cook in slow oven about 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: applesauce oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add the eggs.
Add the applesauce/soda mixture and mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon and add.
Add oatmeal, raisins and nuts last.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets and bake in 400° oven for about 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: steak soup
directions: Put the ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
This should work in deep pot, covered, on low heat for 4 to 5 hours, but a crock-pot is so wonderful and so easy.

title: summer fruit cake(fat-free)
directions: Substitute juice from canned fruit for oil in cake mix.

title: julia's revenge
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
Add rice, onion, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes on low.

title: reduced fat spaghetti pie
directions: In bowl, combine spaghetti, egg substitute and Parmesan cheese. Spoon into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Press against sides and bottom to form crust.
In nonstick skillet, brown turkey, stirring to break up meat.
Add onions and seasonings.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato and tomato sauce, simmer for 5 minutes.
Spread over spaghetti crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 5 more minutes. Makes 6 servings. 236 calories; 122 mg. sodium; 7 grams fat per serving.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add other ingredients and bake in 2 or 3-quart casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: *If you use honey, cut white sugar to 1/2 cup.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, water, strawberry jello, salt and few drops red food coloring together.
Cook until thick.
Cool and pour over cut strawberries in a pie crust that has been baked.

title: yogurt yeast rolls
directions: Mix oil, sugar and yogurt.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt mixture.
Beat 2 cups of flour.
Then add more flour until beaters are heavy.
Take beaters out and continue to add flour and stir with fork until dough can be handled.
Knead until smooth and shiny.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Spray inside plastic storage bags.
Put dough in refrigerator for 8 hours or longer.
Punch down and make into rolls or can make crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Has 66 calories per roll.

title: ranger cookies(gift jar recipe)
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, and baking soda in a medium mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Layer in a 1 quart glass jar or canister the following ingredients: 1/2 of the cereal, flour mixture, brown sugar, remaining cereal and coconut. Tap jar gently on the counter, settle each layer before adding the next. Cover jar. Store at room temperature up to 1 month. Or, attach baking directions and give as a gift.

title: anytime apple crisp
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss sliced apples with 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Add apples to pan.
In large bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Mix with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.

title: pan fried apples
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cover and cook on medium heat until apples are tender.
May substitute equivalent of Sweet 'N Low brown sugar for regular sugar.
Serve warm.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut together and put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut. Melt margarine; add cream cheese and powdered sugar. Put by spoonfuls (around outer edge) on top of cake. Do not spread. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour and 1/2 c. sugar. In another bowl, combine the egg, milk, oil and extract; mix well. Stir into dry ingredients just until combined. Stir in coconut. Fill greased muffin cups two-thirds full. combine sugar, coconut, butter and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter. Bake at 400° for 18-20 minutes.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Makes 3/4 quart.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt white almond bark and peanut butter in double boiler. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper; put in cool place.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place broccoli in a buttered casserole dish.
Melt margarine in a skillet; add onion and celery and cook slowly until onion is transparent.
Add to the broccoli along with the rice, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Cream butter gradually, adding sugar and beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Combine flour and salt, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Makes 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: sausage, cheese and egg pie
directions: Brown sausage in hot skillet until crumbled; drain.
Cover bottom of deep 10-inch pie plate.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over sausage.
Mix Bisquick, slightly beaten eggs and milk; pour over the cheese and sausage.
Bake for 40 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
Insert knife to test for doneness.

title: macaroni and cheese with hot dogs
directions: Boil the hot dogs.
Remove the skins when cooled and cut into diagonal slices.
Cook macaroni in salted water until tender. Rinse in hot water and drain; melt butter in pan.
Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Reduce heat and add milk gradually.
Bring to a boil, stirring continuously.
Reduce heat and cook for 3 minutes.
Add hot dogs, cheese, mustard and salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Add macaroni and mix well.
Pour mixture into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.

title: slow cooker chili
directions: If sausage comes in casing, remove casing.
In large skillet brown sausage and ground beef.
Drain.

title: baked cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rich fudge brownies
directions: Combine sugar and oil; add eggs.
Add vanilla, melted chocolate and nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Sift cake flour and salt together.
Gradually add to chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth. Pour into greased 8-inch square cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken a la alice
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes (oil skins) at 400° for 1 hour or until done. Allow potatoes to cool to touch.
Cut in half lengthwise. Carefully scoop out pulp leaving 1/4 to 1/8-inch shell.
Cut shells in half crosswise and deep fry in hot oil (375°) for 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Place skins on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt, cheese and bacon. Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon margarine in heavy skillet.
Beat
egg
yolks
slightly
and combine with 1/2 cup sugar,
flour
and milk.
Heat and pour into caramelized sugar slowly.
Cook
on medium heat, stirring until all lumps disappear and
mixture
is thick.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine and vanilla. Top
with
meringue
made
with
egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Simmer for 15 minutes. Cool. Add 1/2 cup ketchup.

title: mayo and peas
directions: Drain peas well.
Add enough mayonnaise to cover peas.
Cut up Vienna sausages to bite size and add to peas.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: cheese straws
directions: Allow margarine to soften.
Grate cheese and blend with margarine.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cheese mixture.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool slightly and cut into finger lengths.

title: butter roll
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, shortening, salt and water.
Make crust and divide into 3 pieces and roll each oblong.
Take 1 stick real butter and 1/2 cup sugar and divide equally among the 3 crusts and fold each over.
Bake at 350° until very light brown and crust is done.
Heat 1 1/2 cups sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour over pie crust and cook about 5 minutes.

title: festival rice
directions: In a large frying pan, heat oil.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery until soft.
Add mushrooms, sage, marjoram, thyme and vinegar; simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: after-skating coffee cake
directions: Beat together first four ingredients (reserve 1/2 cup to sprinkle over batter), then add next four ingredients.
Blend well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together. Mix the remaining ingredients together. Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: zesty peas
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add peas with juice and seasoning.
Simmer until peas are hot and juice is about gone.

title: fried turkey
directions: Place shortening in large pot.
Let shortening get hot. Carefully put turkey in hot shortening.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes per pound.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly and spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: salami hor d'oeuvres
directions: Grind salami.
Mix salami and parsley with softened cream cheese. Cut bread in half crosswise and use a long skinny knife to cut out center, leaving about 1/2-inch bread on crusts.

title: banana tea muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly; stir in oil and sugar.
Add bananas and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to banana mixture. Stir just until liquid and dry ingredients are combined.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump a medium size can of crushed pineapple and a can of unsweetened red cherries; stir.
On top of fruit, sprinkle entire box of yellow cake mix.
Bake at 400° for about half hour.
Lower to 350° and bake another half hour until brown and juice is bubbling through cake mix.
Serve warm or cold.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix Jell-O and set aside to cool.
Put cranberries and oranges through food chopper, using medium knife.
Chop nuts with coarse knife.
Add sugar, pineapple and food coloring and combine with Jell-O.
Pour into appropriate containers and refrigerate.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: sarah's mexican flank stew
directions: Dredge steak pieces in flour, salt and pepper and brown in oil.
Remove meat; add onion and cook until golden.
Add other ingredients and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours on top of stove or in oven. Add more chili powder, if you like a lot.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Season flour with salt and pepper.
Heat lard in frying pan until very hot.
Roll rabbit pieces in flour mixture until coated real good.
Fry until brown on all sides.
Cover with water and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: whale tail fudge pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft.
Add milk, sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour warm fudge topping into pie crust and cover with the mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and freeze several hours.

title: big boy slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Toss with cabbage the carrots, dry onion, seasoned salt and milk.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Then mix the mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, mustard and celery.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: arroz con leche carmen
directions: Boil together the first 4 ingredients approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Small amount of water should still be in pot before adding remaining ingredients.
Add the next four ingredients and boil for 1 hour over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove lemon rind and cinnamon sticks.
Place in small serving containers and sprinkle with cinnamon.
A true Cuban delight!!!

title: pat's tasty dressing
directions: Precook onions and celery in enough water to cover while cooking.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add onions, celery and liquid to mixture.
Place in a big baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes a big batch.

title: meat loaf in muffin tins
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Place mixture in muffin tins, filling about 3/4 full.
Bake in 325° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old country ham
directions: Put enough vinegar in mixture until it is stiff.
Spread over top of ham.
Place under broiler until golden brown.

title: gougere
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add flour and stir until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat and continue stirring until mixture cools.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, stirring until mixture is slightly glossy and smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut bread into slices and serve.

title: pea soup
directions: Wash peas in pan. Add 2 quarts water. Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Let peas soak overnight. Add all veggies and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer until tender. Add meat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cover cookie sheets with wax paper.
Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Boil mixture over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto covered cookie sheets.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Heat oven to 375°. Brown meat and drain.
Add corn, salsa, tomato sauce, and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.
In separate bowl combine cottage cheese, eggs, and oregano.
Line bottom of greased 13 x 9 baking dish with 5 tortillas, overlapping edges.
Top with half the meat mixture.
Spoon cottage cheese mixture over meat.
Arrange 5 tortillas over cheese mixture. Spread remaining meat mixture all over and top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and casserole bubbles.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute green pepper and onion with hamburger in frypan.
Drain grease.
In separate saucepan, boil water and rice with salt until done.
Mix together rice, hamburger, pepper and onion.
Add tomato puree, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black bean soup, cuban or jamaican
directions: Soak rinsed beans overnight in water.
Put beans and soaking water into 5-quart pot.
Add ham, celery, garlic, onions, pepper, allspice and beef stock base.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours, or until beans are ready to smash.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: bill's favorite casserole
directions: Bake 4 large potatoes in microwave until done.
Make mashed potatoes out of 2 potatoes, adding 1/2 cup milk and 1/4 cup butter.
Put this mixture in bottom of quart casserole and pat up sides of casserole.

title: cashew chick
directions: In small saucepan, dissolve bouillon in water.
Combine soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and ginger; stir into bouillon mixture. In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Add bouillon mixture; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts and rice.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with nuts.

title: winter's salad
directions: Heat to boiling vinegar, sugar and oil.
Empty all cans and other items.
Mix.
Pour boiling ingredients over.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will last up to 2 weeks.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer. Melt almond bark in microwave, not very long.
Pour over mixture. Mix with mixer again and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan greased lightly with butter.
You can add chopped nuts into fudge if desired.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt alternately with milk, mixed with vanilla and red food coloring.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Put bell pepper, hot pepper, vinegar and sugar in a heavy saucepan; cook together for 7 minutes after it boils.
Take off heat and cool for 5 minutes.
Add Certo.
Stir well.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: e-z ham glaze
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Baste the last 30 minutes that the ham bakes.

title: health salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together and pour over sliced vegetables.
Add 8 ounces Italian dressing to mix.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: jello salad
directions: Place cottage cheese in large mixing bowl.
Mix in dry jello; mix well.
Stir in pineapple bits.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows.
Cool for 2 hours or it may be eaten immediately. You may also add fresh strawberries, raspberries or mandarin oranges, depending on the choice of jello.

title: mozzarella and tomato antipasto
directions: Cut tomatoes and Mozzarella into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate tomato and cheese on a plate.
Drizzle oil and vinegar over tomato and cheese.
Sprinkle basil and pepper over the top.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.

title: hershey fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. While cake is cooking, prepare icing.

title: cheese and chutney(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Let stand at room temperature and mix.
Pour chutney over mixture and then chopped green onion.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add hot water; stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and sugar; chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Mix Dream Whip as on package; add to gelatin mix.
Layer in pan, starting with cake, Dream Whip mixture and coconut.
Repeat. Chill overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
