Cut up and layer in a large casserole dish.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and onion salt; layer over broccoli.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: court bouillon
directions: Make brown roux of oil and flour.
Add onions, celery and garlic; let cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook slowly, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add water and simmer 1 hour.
Add 4 pounds of any firm fish (catfish, red fish or goo) cut in pieces.
Be careful not to cook too much, about 15 minutes. Season to taste and add parsley and onion tops about 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: rhubarb tart
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter with fork until crumbly.
Pat into greased baking dish (11 x 8-inch).
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, salt and 1 stick melted butter. Pour into a long casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake for 45 minutes at 400°. Top with crushed cornflakes and other melted butter. Put back in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham and mac bake
directions: Cook
macaroni	in
boiling
salted water until tender; drain. In saucepan melt 1/4 cup butter; blend in flour, brown sugar, mustard,
salt and pepper.	Add milk all at once; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cooked macaroni, ham
and sliced apples.
Turn mixture into a 2 quart casserole dish. Combine bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons of melted butter. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with sour cream, jiffy corn meal mix and egg. Mix well, then pour in cream corn and whole kernel corn.
(Do not drain water.)
Put in oven.
Cook at 375 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: houma luncheon salad
directions: Combine mushrooms, shrimp, tarragon, garlic and dressing. Chill 1 hour.
Arrange lettuce leaves on individual salad plates. Peel, halve and pit avocados.
Place a half avocado on each plate and fill with salad mixture.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Put melted butter in bottom of oblong pan.
Crumble graham crackers and put in pan; pat into bottom of pan.
Next, in layers, put chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and finally the chopped pecans.
Open can of Eagle Brand milk and pour over the top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine butter, rice, onion and consomme in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and brown for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, toss 1/2 cup chips with flour to coat.
Stir into cheese mixture. Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup chips evenly over top.
Bake 55 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Turn oven off.
Allow cheesecake to cool in oven with door slightly open.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chiperoo bars
directions: Melt
shortening and stir in brown sugar.
Mix well and cool. Sift
together
flour,
baking
powder
and
salt.
To shortening mixture,
add
eggs,
one
at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in chips and
nuts. Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When almost cool, cut into bars.

title: chicken zesta casserole
directions: In a saucepan, saute with oleo the celery, bell pepper and onion.
Place in a large casserole.
Add remaining ingredients; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and chop onions and peppers.
Cover with ice water and salt.
Soak for 3 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix all the ingredients together except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Heat and stir until all ingredients are blended.
Don't overheat,
so
the
oil
doesn't separate.
Pour
over
oyster crackers (16 ounce size).
Mix very well and put out on cookie sheet in a 275° oven for 13 minutes or
a
little
less.
Stir frequently.
Cool completely, then store
in airtight container.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is gone.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken obscenity
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown chicken in oil.
Add garlic and onions.
Let brown and add lemon juice.
Bake in covered pan for 1 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Bake in 2 round cake pans.
Let cool.
Mix pudding according to directions; set aside.
Mix 1 cup hot water with Jell-O.
Add frozen strawberries to Jell-O, then layer as follows in punch bowl:
1/2 pudding, 1 cake round, 1/2 strawberry and Jell-O mixture, 1 cake round, remaining strawberry and Jell-O mixture, then the remaining pudding.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with nuts and strawberry halves.

title: pat's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg. Stir in dissolved yeast and add flour.
Beat until combined. Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Turn out on floured surface and roll into desired shapes; or after mixing refrigerate overnight and roll out.
Let rise 1 to 2 hours and cook at 375° until brown and brush with melted butter.

title: angel-flaked biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Blend Crisco with dry ingredients with pastry cutter.
Combine yeast mixture with buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients, making a stiff dough.
Place in covered container and store in refrigerator.
Pinch off dough as needed.
Place biscuits on cookie sheet in cold oven; turn to 450°.
As oven warms to baking temperature, biscuits rise and bake.
This dough can be kept in refrigerator 1 to 2 weeks.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain. Boil egg noodles until tender; drain.
Put in a large mixing bowl.
Add cream of chicken and tomato soups.
Mix well.
Melt cheese in saucepan.
Pour over noodle mixture.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar together in large mixing bowl.
Mix eggs and oil together in smaller bowl and add to dry ingredients.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in the bottom of a medium sized casserole or deep dish pie pan.
Combine salsa and chili.
Spread on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve hot with chips.

title: ranch beans
directions: Saute beef and onions in melted margarine until beef is browned.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine sugar and catsup.
Add to beans and beef mixture.
Turn into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: microwave cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat oil in pie plate until very hot, about 5 to 7 minutes. Place each tortilla in hot oil to make it more pliable.

Combine mixed cheeses, 1/2 cup green onions and chopped olives in a bowl. Place about 2 tablespoons of this mixture into each tortilla. Roll closed and place seam-side down in an 8 x 12-inch shallow baking dish.
Pour enchilada sauce over top and sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese and 1/3 cup chopped green onion on top.
Microwave at 80% power (Medium-high) for 13 to 15 minutes, turning dish once during cooking.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad in a flash
directions: Toss all ingredients together, chill and serve.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Melt margarine; add flour.
Add next 3 ingredients and stir until bubbly.
Continue to cook until white sauce thickens.
Add chicken, noodles and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry the sausage and drain off fat.
Saute celery and onion. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Lay bacon strips on top (optional). Bake one hour or more at 350°, uncovered.

title: judy's pepper steak
directions: Cut steak with kitchen shears into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Heat oil in skillet; add garlic, salt and pepper.
Saute until garlic is golden.
Add steak slices; brown slightly for 2 minutes.
Remove meat.
Add green peppers and onions; cook 3 minutes.
Return beef to pan; add soy sauce, sugar, bouillon and green onions.
Also add water chestnuts and cornstarch (dissolved in cold water).
Simmer about 2 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; follow box directions.
Let cool.
Add crushed pineapple (not drained).
Add cottage cheese; stir until well mixed.
Sprinkle top with pecans.
Place in icebox until congealed.
Cut in squares.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer ingredients in this order:
1) shredded lettuce, 2) drained peas, 3) shallots, 4) sliced eggs, 5) drained water chestnuts and 6) bacon bits.
Mix and seal salad with sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Refrigerate.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar and garlic salt.
Pour over raw vegetables.
Let set overnight.
Keeps for several days.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: In
large
kettle,
cover
shanks
with
water; heat to boiling.
Add
bay leaves and peppercorns.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 3/4 hours or until meat is tender. Remove shanks, cut meat
into 1/2-inch cubes.
Let stock cool slightly.
Skim fat from surface;
strain stock and return to kettle. Add meat and remaining
ingredients;
heat
to
boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump pineapple and cherry pie filling in pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Crumble margarine and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until crunchy.

title: easy chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend all and beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Pour in greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp scampi(serves 4)
directions: Preheat broiler to highest temperature.
Use a pan big enough to hold shrimp in one layer.
Melt butter.
Stir in olive oil, lemon juice, shallots, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and coat completely with butter.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes, then turn and broil 4 to 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle parsley and serve.

title: sheath cake
directions: Mix together and set aside flour and sugar in large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, mix margarine, 4 tablespoons of cocoa and 1 cup of water.
Bring this mixture to a rapid boil and pour over sugar and flour; mix well.
Then add buttermilk, soda, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 slightly beaten eggs.
Mix all this well and pour in a long, greased and floured pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° to 400°.
Pour icing on hot cake.

title: mini cinni's
directions: Unroll dough, and separate into 4 rectangles; pinch seams to seal.
Stir together sugar and cinnamon, and sprinkle evenly over rectangles.
Small amount of pecans can be sprinkled over sugar/cinnamon, if desired.
Roll up, jellyroll fashion, starting with a long side; press edges to seal.
Cut each log into 7 to 8 slices, and place in a lightly greased 8-inch round cake pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Glaze while warm.
Makes 28 to 32 rolls.

title: mt. pilot pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix and cook for 5 minutes;
cool and freeze.

title: toffee fudge
directions: Sprinkle pecans on bottom of a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Combine
sugar
and
butter
in
a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook and
stir constantly for 7 minutes at a low boil.
Remove from heat.
Spread over pecans.
Place pieces of chocolate bar over
the
top,
spreading
it
as it melts.
Cut into squares while fairly warm and refrigerate to keep.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Mix altogether.
Mix with mixer on high for 10 minutes.

title: crepes(french pancakes)
directions: Place flour in a bowl.
Make a hole.
Put in it the whole eggs, oil, salt and a little milk.
Mix well with a spoon. Progressively, add the milk until mixture makes a ribbon when you pour it from the spoon.
Add the flavoring of your choice (vanilla or lemon juice).
Let the mixture sit for 1 hour.
It will become thicker.
Add a little milk to make it thinner.
Put just a little oil (Pam is better) on a very hot pancake griddle or skillet.
A round Teflon skillet with the bottom the desired size of the pancake is best.
Make the mixture spread out by moving and turning skillet vigorously.
Turn the crepe as soon as it's brown and it is done enough to be turned.
This takes less than a minute.
Cook it on the other side.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve hot.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Cook apples and make 5 cups of applesauce.
Cook all ingredients in crock-pot for 20 hours on low heat.
Seal in warm jars.

title: bite size quiches
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, mayonnaise, onion and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted and creamy.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add small amount of warm cream cheese to beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Add remaining mixture.
Add olives, sausage and Swiss cheese.
Mix well.
Coat tart pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Fill each cup to the top.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool. Remove from pan and cool completely.
To reheat, use 275° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and stir until smooth. Add syrup and sugar and boil for 3 minutes; cool. Add beaten eggs and nuts; blend well. Pour into pie shell; bake for 10 minutes at 450°; reduce oven to 350° and bake for an additional 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spam casserole
directions: Grease a large bowl.
Mix ingredients all together. Stir in milk, making it soupy. Bake in a 350° oven, stirring twice. This makes enough for two meals or put half in freezer for another time.

title: pepsi-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in a bowl.
Heat butter, marshmallows, cocoa and Pepsi-Cola together.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Put soda in milk and add. Then add the vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut joys
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and coconut.
Mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoonful of mixture into a ball.
Make indent in center of each ball and place on a cookie sheet.
Fill centers with melted chocolate.
Chill until firm. Store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows, cool, then add frozen strawberries (with juice), pineapple and bananas.
Put half the mixture in flat dish.
Let jell, then cover with sour cream. Add remaining half of mixture and put in refrigerator until jelled.

title: banana nut bread(makes 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Put cream cheese and eggs in small mixer bowl; blend at low speed until smooth.
Add mashed bananas; mix well.
Place half of dry cake mix in large bowl. Add banana mixture and beat until blended.
Add remaining cake mix and nuts; stir until just blended.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans on racks 20 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely on racks.

title: zucchini crisp
directions: Mix the ingredients together; simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into baking dish; set aside.

title: don's salted nut roll bars
directions: Melt the first 2 ingredients very slowly on low heat.
Add the milk and marshmallows.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 jar nuts on bottom. Add melted mixture and rest of nuts.
Press in pan and refrigerate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press out on cookie sheet, pressing edges and seams together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together. Spread on baked rolls.
Top with the grated carrots, broccoli and cauliflower.
Sprinkle top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: creme brulee
directions: Pour caramel into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Blend all other ingredients in blender.
Pour over caramel layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in pan of water. Cool. Refrigerate overnight.
Invert and serve.

title: microwave meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Shape into balls about 1 1/2 inches in size.
Place meatballs in an 8 x 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover loosely with wax paper and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Rearrange meatballs; microwave another 6 minutes.
Let stand for 3 minutes; drain. Makes about 24 meatballs.

title: lime salad(this can almost pass as a dessert)
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Boil, then add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Mix marshmallows and cream cheese.
Pour jello in slowly and mix until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and nuts; fold in Cool Whip. Pour into mold and refrigerate.
Will keep and taste good for 2 weeks.
Nice for a Christmas salad.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Add sugar and beat well with a fork. Add Karo and beat again with a fork.
Then, add melted butter and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies or 1 deep dish pie.

title: wild rice shrimp casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mrs. chiles' sweet 'n sour italian dressing
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Add dressing mix, then ice, stirring until ice melts. Add oil. Store, covered, in the refrigerator. Shake well before pouring.

title: apple crumble pie
directions: Prepare and roll out pastry.
Line a 9-inch pie plate.
Trim pastry to 1/2-inch beyond edge.
Flute edge; do not prick.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook rice as directed and set aside.
Mix 2 sticks oleo, melted, and chopped onions and saute.
Combine sweet milk, flour and soup.
Cook and debone chicken.
Put together in the following layers:
half of the mixed sauce, rice, chicken, cheese and other half of sauce.
Bake in oven 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put flour in large bowl and hollow out center.
Add the remaining ingredients in the middle and mix ingredients with hands like making bread.
Add more flour as needed to make it doughy. Roll on flat, floured surface.
Cut cookies and sprinkle with sugar.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake approximately 7 minutes.

title: joann's jalapeno glazed turkey breast
directions: Grill turkey until done.
In a saucepan combine remaining ingredients; heat over medium heat and stir until thickened.
Brush turkey with sauce during last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking.
Serve remaining sauce over sliced turkey.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach, drain and chopped into small pieces. Beat eggs with oil and cheese. Add onions, peppers and spinach.
Bake at 325° for 20 - 25 min.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa in bowl.
In other bowl, cream oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each egg.
Add food color.
Mix well.
In 3rd bowl, combine buttermilk and soda; mix well.
Add to oil/sugar mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured pans (8 or 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions gently until transparent.
In a large bowl, combine stuffing mix, soup and sour cream.
Fold in onions. Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish and top
with more stuffing mix.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: tornado explorer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla extract; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Press candy Kisses in center of cookies, as soon as out of the oven.
Bake these cookies 6 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned on bottom; do not overbake.
Cool.
Store in a tightly covered jar at room temperature.
Makes 3 dozen to 40 cookies usually.
Great with coffee, also!

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: jean's salad
directions: Wash and cut tomatoes in half.
Place in a bowl.
Peel and slice the onion.
Add to tomatoes.
Cube the Mozzarella cheese. Chop the bell pepper and add these to tomatoes and onion.
Toss with dressing.
This is best if made the day before and allowed to marinate overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Grease baking dish and cover with Tater Tots.
Sprinkle chopped onion on top.
Melt cheese and sour cream and pour over. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 230°.

title: apple tortillas
directions: Roll up filling in tortillas.
Place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Dissolve sugar and butter in water.
Pour over tortillas.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Stir in green chilies.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Cake:
Drain mandarin oranges, saving juice.
Mix cake according to box directions, but use mandarin orange juice instead of water.
Add 1 1/2 cans of mandarin oranges.
Beat well and bake as directed on cake box.
Cool in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: momma's mexican skillet
directions: Lightly brown meat; drain fat.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in macaroni and next 4 ingredients. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: three star chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place in shallow baking dish or pan.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Spread over chicken. Bake, lightly covered, at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Place cooked and peeled sweet potatoes in a bowl, add oleo, syrup, sugars, and eggs; mix well. Add vanilla, cinnamon, cream, and salt; mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Yields 3 (9 inch) pies or 2 (10 inch) pies.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Roast beef and cool.
In large skillet cook onion in oleo.
Add water, catsup, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and mustard.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Slice beef thin and add to sauce, heat thoroughly.
Serve on small buns.
If using a large roast, double or triple sauce recipe.
Every one asks for this recipe.

title: kid's play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add drops of food coloring until desired color.
Store in Ziploc bags. May be stored in freezer until ready to play with.

title: mock eclairs
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When cool, cut cake into 16 (4 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) pieces. Cut each piece in half, lengthwise.
Spread 1 tablespoon of pudding between split cake pieces and top with chocolate fudge topping.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together except reserve margarine and bread, pour into well greased 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread and margarine.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Slice peppers and cheese; arrange in two layers in baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients and pour over cheese and chili peppers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Arrange pineapple, bananas and marshmallows in bottom of long flat dish or pan. Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Pour over fruit. Chill until firm.
Cook pineapple juice, butter, egg and sugar until thick. Add Dream Whip.
Spread over Jell-O. Chill. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Mix crawfish tails, fat, vegetables and salt and pepper.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Pour cooking oil in thick pot.
Heat oil to very hot.
Add all ingredients and cover for 8 minutes.
Stir and reduce heat.
Cook for 7 minutes.
Serve over rice with green salad and garlic bread.

title: grandma's onion salad
directions: Smash crackers.
Add chopped onion.
Mix together milk, vinegar and Miracle Whip.
Pour over crackers and onions.
Stir. Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with sliced eggs.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange 1/3 potatoes in overlapping slices in large oven to table dish (9 x 13-inch) sprayed with vegetable spray.
Generously season potatoes with salt and pepper and 1/3 of the thyme and 1/3 of cheese.
Top with 2 more layers potatoes, seasonings and cheese.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; mix together and press into pan.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, walnuts and flaked coconut.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Heat liquid drained from artichokes in a skillet over medium heat with onion and garlic salt.
Saute onion until tender. Starting with beaten eggs, add remaining ingredients including chopped artichokes.
Add ingredients from skillet.	Pour into buttered 9 x13 pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares, serve warm.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in melted margarine.
Butter casserole dish and add rice, consomme and bouillon.
Drain mushrooms.
Add mushrooms and onion to casserole.
Cook (uncovered) at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: s. o. s.
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Place into a large saucepan.
Add butter and flour.
Mix until butter is melted.
Be sure flour does not stick.
Cook over medium heat.
Add 1 cup milk at a time, until ground beef floats.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Serve on warm toast.

title: ground-beef stew with cornmeal dumplings
directions: To Make Stew:

Shape ground beef into 4 large patties. Fry in a heavy Dutch oven until rare or medium done. Drain off excess fat and break patties in the pan into pieces. Add onion, pepper and garlic and saute with meat for a few minutes until limp.
Add tomatoes, water, oregano and cumin. Simmer, breaking up chunks of tomatoes with the back of a spoon. While the stew cooks, make dumplings.

title: nanny's raisin cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 2 or 3 times.
Mix in buttermilk and margarine.
Add raisins, leaving enough to cover cake.
Pour into three round cake pans.
Bake at 325° until done (ovens vary, do not overcook).

title: taco supreme dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add taco mix and water; simmer 15 minutes.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish with refried beans.
Pour beef mixture over beans; spread out.
Spread sour cream over beef mixture.
Cut up green onions; sprinkle over mixture.
Add sliced jalapeno peppers and shredded cheese; sprinkle diced tomatoes over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with plain Doritos or tostados.

title: lucy's sunday night supper for two or twenty (lucille ball)
directions: Brown the meat in butter and add sauteed chopped onions, green pepper and garlic.
Put to a slow simmer.
Add canned tomatoes plus juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Accent.
Last 1/2 hour, add cooked, strained egg noodles.
Serve with salad, garlic-buttered, heated French bread and dessert of your choice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash and soak beans.
Cook until tender; drain.
Add onion, sugars, mustard and vinegar.
Add enough molasses to color tan. Cover with few strips bacon; drizzle with catsup.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix and chill. Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well with beater.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake about 25 minutes at 325°.
Top with sour cream sweetened to taste or use fruit pie filling.

title: squash casserole
directions: Set aside enough grated cheese and cracker crumbs to cover casserole.
Boil sliced
squash in small amount of water, with salt and sugar.
Cover and cook until tender.
Drain well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining grated cheese and cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 325 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican pork tacos
directions: In a frypan, add oil and saute onion until limp.
Stir in pork, chiles, raisins, olives and enchilada sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, until pork is cooked, approximately 15 minutes, stirring to blend.
Use for tacos.
It tastes great with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
The chiles and enchilada sauce come in different degrees of hotness.
Even the mild has quite a zing!
No need to add additional hot sauce.
Besides, it hides the flavor of the fillings.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Place 2 rounded spoonfuls in a cup and fill with boiling water.
Store mix in a container with a tight fitting lid.

title: black bean and corn salsa
directions: Combine ingredients. Chill one hour, or until ready to serve. Serve with tortilla chips or as a
baked potato topping.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in large frying pan.
Drain excess fat.
Mix in tomato paste and mixed vegetables.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put in large round dish, put mashed potatoes on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: italian fish casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix according to box instructions.
Cut up sausage into small pieces and mix into the stuffing, spread this in bottom of dish.
Place fish on top of stuffing then pour sauce over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until you can flake fish with a fork.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion; drain grease.
Add corn, spices, and sauce.
Line baking dish with tortillas, meat, cheese, and peppers (usually two layers).
Cook at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: onion chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place onion soup and bread crumbs in large plastic bag and shake to blend.
Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place one piece of chicken in bag at a time, close tightly and shake until coated.
Place chicken on rack in broiler pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Serves 4.

title: lazy pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, mix cottage cheese, egg and onion salt together and spoon over noodles.
Cover with layer of noodles.
Mix together Cheddar cheese, potatoes, salt and pepper and spread over noodles.
Cover with another layer of noodles.
Melt butter and saute onions in frying pan until onions are clear and soft.
Pour over noodles. Cover.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serve with sour cream.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli, chicken, soup, mayo, milk, cheese and lemon juice in a lightly greased casserole dish; cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook macaroni 7 minutes.
Boil shrimp 3 minutes.
Add chopped celery, relish or chopped pickles, bell pepper, salt, pepper, Accent, mayonnaise and mustard.

title: champagne sherbet punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Just before serving, scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Add champagne. Stir gently.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: rio grande pork roast
directions: Mix together the salt, garlic salt and 1/2 teaspoon chili powder.
Rub the meat well with this mixture.
Place the pork roast, flat on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: mushroom appetizers on toasted batard bread
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Stir in flour. When mushrooms are golden and tender, remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and dry onion soup. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be made the day before.
This is good served on Toasted Batard Bread.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix first 4 ingredients and bake at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix next ingredients and cover over cake.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine until smooth; add powdered sugar and mix well.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add nuts. Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: wacky cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Dissolve baking soda in vinegar; put everything in one bowl and mix well.
Bake in 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: spicy cabbage casserole
directions: In a deep heavy skillet over moderately high heat, combine the beef, onion, garlic, bell pepper, oregano, salt and pepper, stirring constantly until brown.
Add the tomatoes, tomato sauce and rice and mix thoroughly.
In a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole, arrange layers of the meat mixture, the cabbage and the cheese. Bake the casserole, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tea cakes
directions: Use enough flour to make dough stiff to roll.
Roll out and cut.
Bake until brown.

title: pancit
directions: Take chicken breast and boil in 2 cups water with 2 chicken bouillon.
Saute garlic, onion and shredded chicken in oil.
Add broth, soy sauce, pepper and paprika and let simmer for 3 minutes. Add carrots and celery.
Let it cook 3 minutes.
While cooking, soak noodles in lukewarm water for 2 minutes, then drain.
Add noodles and cabbage and continue cooking and stirring until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: On each tortilla shell, evenly divide and spread down center one can of refried beans and the ground beef. Roll up, tucking in ends as you roll.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam. Spread one can of refried beans on top.
Pour enchilada sauce over. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes until cheese melts and casserole heats through.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut off all fat on steak and put in a casserole dish.
Mix all the other ingredients well and pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Cover and bake for 1 hour more. Drain.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Toss all ingredients, then pour Salad Dressing over salad and toss gently.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese and powdered sugar, then add peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Put nuts, chocolate chips or cookie crumbs on top, if you wish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries and orange with peel through food chopper using fine blade.
Add sugar and let stand one hour.
Then add one cup hot water to gelatin and dissolve.
When mixture begins to congeal, then add cranberries, pecans, celery and fruit.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Then eat!

title: baked broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until you can cut with fork.
Drain.
Stir in cheese and 1/2 margarine until melted.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Melt remaining margarine and stir in Ritz crackers.
Put cracker mixture over cabbage and bake until brown on top (about 25 minutes in 350° oven).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in casserole.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May add turkey or chicken.

title: spicy citrus cooler
directions: Bring water to boil.
Place tea, cloves and cinnamon in teapot.
Pour boiling water over tea mixture.
Cover; let stand about 10 minutes.
In a 2-quart nonmetal container, combine grapefruit juice and orange juice concentrate.
Remove tea bags and strain spices from tea; pour into juice mixture.
Refrigerate. Serve over ice, stirring to combine.
Garnish as desired. Servings:
Serving size:
1 cup.

title: easy oven chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix ketchup with cola and pour over chicken. Bake until tender, about 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar bread pudding
directions: Mix together in bowl, brown and white sugars, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Fold in bread cubes and lightly beaten eggs.
Pour into greased 1 quart baking dish.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 325° until inverted knife comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add eggs, continue beating.
Add bananas and vanilla, mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the mixture.
Blend.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into prepared 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: super sloppy joshes
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off any excess fat.
Stir in the prepared mustard, chili powder and salt.
Cook and stir for 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, tomato juice and shredded carrots. Bring mixture to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer meat mixture, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook about three minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes (do not use any milk).
Add all other ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until slightly dry or brown looking on top.
It will probably bubble on sides.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix ingredients in pan with fork; beat one minute.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes. Run knife around edges of pan to remove.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: In double boiler mix sugar and flour.
Add chocolate and butter.
Combine milk and egg to mixture.
Stir constantly.
When mixture thickens, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir well. Pool filling into cooled, baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake at 400° approximately 5 minutes.

title: garlic toast
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Shake a small amount of garlic salt on both sides.
Place in heated frypan until golden brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: corn pone
directions: Mix well.
Grease a tube pan.
Let stand until it begins to bubble (2 to 4 hours).
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a medium oven.
Scald with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 2 cups medium hot water.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix hot water, Kool-Aid and Jell-O together.
Add sugar and cold water.
Pour into ice trays or popsicle holders.
Freeze for at least 5 hours.

title: onion blossom
directions: Peel onion, leaving root end intact. Cut vertically into quarters. Cut to 1/2-inch of root end. Cut each quarter vertically into thirds and place onion in boiling water 1 minute. Remove and place in ice water 5 minutes. Loosen "petals" if necessary. Drain, cut side down. Place flour in Ziploc bag. Add onion; shake well. Dip onion in egg. Place cracker crumbs in bag. Add onion, tossing to coat. Chill 1 hour. Pour oil to depth of 3-inches into electric fryer or saucepan and heat to 375°. Fry onion 5 to 7 minutes or until golden. Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt. Serve with honey mustard or Ranch. Makes 2 appetizer servings.

title: cauliflower-cashew soup
directions: Combine water/stock, onion, carrot, cauliflower and garlic in soup pot.
Bring to simmer and cook until tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Add pepper and tarragon.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Place cashews and soup in food processor and puree until smooth.
Combine soup in pot and heat.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandma murrie's oil pastry
directions: Double recipe for 2 crust pie.

title: robert redford torte
directions: Mix the 2/3 cup chopped nuts, flour and melted margarine until crumbly.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese.
Add the powdered sugar and peanut butter; cream until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip; spread on first layer.
Mix the pudding mixes with the milk; spread over second layer.
Spread the Cool Whip on third layer. Garnish with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix all ingredients; chill. Roll into ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: margie kitchen's almond rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put rice, almonds and butter in heavy skillet.
Brown slightly, stirring constantly.
Add chicken broth and place in baking dish.
Cover; cook 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 30 minutes more.

title: supreme chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water over low heat.
Cool.
Beat egg yolks with cream.
Gradually add sugar and beat vigorously until thick. Add chocolate mixture and vanilla, mixing well.

title: jello pie
directions: Line bottom of crust with fruit. Mix Jell-O and pudding with 1 1/2 cups of water and stir with wire whisk until mixed good. Put on heat and stir with wooden spoon until it starts to thicken. Pour over fruit. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: lemon veal
directions: Dip veal in flour; pan-fry in melted butter and oil for 1 minute per side.
Remove to tray.
Put mushrooms in pan and stir until soft, not browned; add lemon juice to pan and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over veal; top with lemon slices and parsley. Serves 4.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco 3 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: bread pudding("a real treat made with leftover biscuits")
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and salt. Add dry bread and raisins.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: peanut butter apple dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients; mix well. Serve with apples. Store in the refrigerator. Yield: 2 2/3 cups.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in pan or Pyrex dish.
Add crushed vanilla wafers.
Mix and press in dish.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour condensed milk on top.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cut into squares.
Freezes well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Use 4-quart pan to cook in as will boil up.
Mix and heat first 4 ingredients until sugar dissolves.
When it comes to a boil, add peanuts.
Cook until it comes to hard crack stage (300° on candy thermometer).
Take off heat.
Add vanilla, margarine and baking soda.
Will fizz so be sure to use large pan.
Stir quickly.
Pour immediately into cookie sheets lined with greased Reynolds aluminum wrap (heavy-duty).
Spread as thin as you can. Cool.

title: shrimp cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to make mixture creamy.
Serve with crackers or make tea sandwiches.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in large baking dish.
Cover with cheese. Combine soup, milk and pimentos and pour over asparagus mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place onion rings on top and bake 10 minutes more.
May add small can of mushroom pieces.

title: coconut cake or cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Add small amounts of milk to make this a sticky ball.
(Note:
When using butter, cut the butter in small pieces.
Using oil, knead first, then decide if there is a need for milk.)
Roll pastry out to about 1 cm (3/8-inch) on cookie sheet; bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Top of cake should be golden brown.
Cut into squares while warm, or form little balls of dough and spread these out on cookie sheet.
These will form cookies about 1 to 1 1/2 inches diameter.
Top with sliced almonds, if desired, before baking.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Break cornbread into pieces in large salad bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours or longer before serving.

title: heavenly apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in hot water.
Add pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, apples and nuts. Let set.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken with beef and a slice of bacon. Arrange in a greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all; refrigerate.
When ready, bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.
Serves 8.
Can be made 2 days ahead.

title: mac 'n cabbage
directions: Combine macaroni, cucumber, cabbage, celery, green onions and tomatoes in a large glass bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over macaroni mixture and toss. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours for flavors to blend.
Makes 12 servings.
